  <li>Support audit readiness and documentation for regulatory or grant reporting requirements</li>
  <li>Identify and implement improvements to accounting workflows, leveraging systems and automation to scale with company growth</li>
  <li>Other duties as assigned<br><br></li>
 </ul><strong>Who You Are<br><br></strong>
 <ul>
  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, Business, or a related field or equivalent experience</li>
  <li>5+ years of progressive accounting experience, preferably in a regulated industry such as life sciences or medical devices</li>
  <li>2+ years of experience processing multi-state payroll</li>
  <li>Passion for being involved in improving processes and applying automation through cross-team collaboration and leveraging technology</li>
  <li>Excellent analytical, oral, and written communication skills are required for frequent interaction with financial and non-financial colleagues, as well as external customers</li>
  <li>Attention to detail, strong planning and organization skills, and the ability to multi-task, prioritize and deliver in a fast-paced, dynamic environment</li>
  <li>Solid understanding of GAAP, payroll laws, and sales tax compliance</li>
  <li>Ability to work autonomously as well as in a team setting</li>
  <li>Takes ownership of quality and deadlines</li>
  <li>Advanced Excel skills, including pivot tables, XLOOKUPs, and complex spreadsheet modeling</li>
  <li>Strong proficiency business systems, such as QuickBooks, Paylocity, Expensify, Avalara, Salesforce or similar types of software</li>
  <li>High level of integrity, professionalism, and commitment to maintaining confidentiality<br><br></li>
 </ul><strong>What We Offer<br><br></strong>$80,000/yr - $115,000/yr base salary + Stock Options
 <br>
 <br>
 We offer competitive compensation, benefits and a fantastic work environment:
 <br>
 <br>
 <ul>
  <li>100% paid Medical, Dental &amp; Vision for employees and generous subsidy for dependents</li>
  <li>11 Paid Holidays and generous Time Off policies</li>
  <li>401K + Employer Match</li>
  <li>Paid parental leave policy</li>
  <li>This position is based in Seattle on Lower Queen Anne, with the option for hybrid work after onboarding<br><br></li>
 </ul>We have a strong healthcare-driven mission, and your guidance and efforts will directly link to our success. We embrace diversity and equal opportunity and are committed to building a team that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. The more inclusive we are, the better our work will be for it.
