INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (46, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline/jobs/50346487-director-of-financial-operations#content', 'Director of Financial Operations', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkFjY291bnRpbmclMjAlMjYlMjBGaW5hbmNlIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/716c870c-b07d-50ff-ab75-427af872bf20-1740432205', 'Zipline', 'Accounting & Finance', 1746489600, '<h2><strong>About Zipline</strong></h2>
<p>Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building, manufacturing and operating the first instant delivery and logistics system that serves all humans equally, wherever they are. From powering Rwanda’s national blood delivery network and Ghana’s COVID-19 vaccine distribution, to providing on-demand home delivery for Walmart, to enabling healthcare providers to bring care directly to U.S. homes, we are transforming the way things move for businesses, governments and consumers. The technology is complex but the idea is simple: a teleportation service that delivers what you need, when you need it. Through our technology that includes robotics and autonomy, we are decarbonizing delivery, decreasing road congestion, and reducing fossil fuel consumption and air pollution, while providing equitable access to billions of people and building a more resilient global supply chain.</p>
<p>Join Zipline and help us to make good on our promise to build an equitable and more resilient global supply chain for billions of people.</p>
<h2><strong>About The Role</strong></h2>
<p>We are excited about bringing in an experienced and motivated Director of Financial Operations to join our fast-paced global Accounting and Finance team! This position is responsible for overseeing financial transactions and processes with an initial focus on procure to pay and customer billings. This role is responsible for leading Zipline through its growth, international expansion and product launches.</p>
<h2><strong>What You\'ll Do</strong></h2>
<ul>
 <li>Own and drive the implementation and improvement of financial operations systems, including purchasing, travel and expense, and billing systems and their related integration into Zipline’s ERP system (NetSuite, Coupa, Navan, Expensify, Divvy expense cards).</li>
 <li>Lead the Procure to Pay and Accounts Receivable teams while overseeing all procure to pay processes, including owing purchase order processes for both manufacturing purchases and indirect spend.</li>
 <li>Build out the global billing function of Zipline with expected substantial ramp of billing operations in 2026 and going forward. Experience with grant billing and tracking are a plus.</li>
 <li>Partner with business leaders to design and implement scalable and efficient financial processes. Drive continuous improvement initiatives to optimize financial operations that align the company’s expected growth.</li>
 <li>Oversee financial transactions and controls related to transaction processing while ensuring compliance with statutory and regulatory reporting requirements.</li>
 <li>Develop financial operational metrics with meaningful data that helps manage the efficiency and growth of the business.</li>
 <li>Collaborate with internal Zipline business partners, with substantial cross-functional teamwork with Zipline’s people, accounting, strategic finance, legal, and product teams.</li>
 <li>Own business relationships with external providers, including travel and expense providers, procurement providers, and other financial shared services providers over time.</li>
 <li>Oversee finance help desk and own financial policy documents with respect to procure to pay and customer billing.</li>
 <li>Lead training efforts across the company to drive the adoption and optimal usage of Zipline’s transactional systems.</li>
 <li>In partnership with the people team, manage master data across multiple systems to ensure consistency of data and integrity of system integrations.</li>
 <li>Design internal processes and partner with Zipline’s applications team to implement system enhancements while ensuring scalability and employee experiences are optimized.</li>
 <li>This position will initially manage and mentor a small team, with the expectation that this person will build and lead a large global financial shared services team as Zipline grows.</li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>What You\'ll Bring</strong></h2>
<ul>
 <li>You have 12+ years of experience in progressive operational financial shared services and financial operations experience. You are willing and able to roll your sleeves up as well as provide strategic direction on financial operational matters.</li>
 <li>You have substantial systems experience with a proven track record in implementing and improving systems at companies with significant growth.</li>
 <li>You have significant experience working in operationally complex businesses, preferably with international experience.</li>
 <li>You are excited about working for a transformative company.</li>
 <li>Ideally, you’ve spent some time working in a public accounting firm and/or have meaningful experience at a company that has gone through significant growth.</li>
 <li>You are comfortable working in highly global and cross-functional environments, able to navigate seamlessly between different functions, cultures and perspectives.</li>
 <li>You can communicate effectively, both verbally and in writing, to build strong relationships with Zipline teams.</li>
 <li>You like to get into the weeds and understand how businesses operate.</li>
 <li>You are capable of working with imperfect information and driving to effective decision making in a fast-paced environment.</li>
 <li>You have solid knowledge of financial statements, accounting principles and financial analysis.</li>
 <li>Ability to periodically travel internationally.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>What Else You Need to Know</strong></h3>
<p>This role is based out of our South San Francisco HQ. Must be eligible to work in the US and travel globally as needed.</p>
<p><span>The starting cash range for this role is $200,000 - $235,000. Please note that this is a target, starting cash range for a candidate who meets the minimum qualifications for this role. The final cash pay for this role will depend on a variety of factors, including a specific candidate\'s experience, qualifications, skills, working location, and projected impact. The total compensation package for this role may also include: equity compensation; overtime pay; discretionary annual or performance bonuses; sales incentives; benefits such as medical, dental and vision insurance; paid time off; and more.</span></p>
<p>Zipline is an equal opportunity employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, ancestry, national origin, religion or religious creed, mental or physical disability, medical condition, genetic information, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, and related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital status, military or veteran status, citizenship, or other characteristics protected by state, federal or local law or our other policies.</p>
<p>We value diversity at Zipline and welcome applications from those who are traditionally underrepresented in tech. If you like the sound of this position but are not sure if you are the perfect fit, please apply!</p>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (47, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/degreed/jobs/50346331-financial-analyst#content', 'Financial Analyst', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/degreed?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkFjY291bnRpbmclMjAlMjYlMjBGaW5hbmNlIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/3517b513-9fb4-53be-a1d7-0cc5a8b33f3e-1747444857', 'Degreed', 'Accounting & Finance', 1746489600, '<div>
 <p>Degreed is the upskilling platform that fuels growth and innovation through lifelong learning. We bring together everything you need to learn and advance—LMSs, courses, videos, articles, projects, and real-world skill insights—and match you with opportunities that align with your skills, role, and goals.</p>
 <p>For businesses, Degreed helps build a culture of learning that attracts, develops, and retains top talent—driving both individual and company success.</p>
 <p>We believe learning is the key to unlocking opportunities. Our mission is to discover, empower, and celebrate the next generation of global expertise.</p>
 <p>Join us in shaping the future of learning and workforce development.</p>
</div>
<p><br>
 Degreed is seeking a detail-oriented <strong>Financial Analyst</strong> to take <strong>primary ownership of our end-to-end sales commission process.</strong> This is a critical role where your work directly impacts the business by <strong>ensuring our global sales teams are accurately and fairly compensated</strong>, reinforcing behaviors that drive bookings and retention, <strong>maintaining the integrity of crucial ARR data</strong> used for valuation and board reporting, and supporting executive decision-making through accurate analysis. While commissions are the core focus, you will also support broader <strong>FP&amp;A functions</strong>, partnering across the business.</p>
<p>We are seeking candidates local to the <strong>Draper, Utah</strong> area for this role. This position follows a hybrid model, requiring presence in our Draper office <strong>2-3 days per week</strong>.<br><br></p>
<p><strong>Key Skills</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Up to 3 years of experience in <strong>commission analysis</strong>, <strong>compensation planning</strong>, or financial analysis - SaaS experience strongly preferred.</li>
 <li>Strong attention to detail, ownership mentality and ability for process improvement and potentially automation.</li>
 <li>Proven ability to analyze complex data, identify trends or discrepancies, and provide actionable insights; strong<strong> Excel </strong>skills are required, and<strong> SQL </strong>proficiency is highly desired.</li>
 <li>Familiarity with <strong>Salesforce</strong>, <strong>NetSuite</strong>, and commission/BI tools like <strong>Xactly, Adaptive Insights, Planful, or Tableau</strong> is highly valued.</li>
 <li>Understanding of key <strong>FP&amp;A principles</strong> and financial statements.</li>
 <li>Experience working across teams and translating technical/contractual terms into practical business guidance.</li>
 <li>Experience with or interest in using <strong>AI to streamline finance workflows</strong>.<br><br></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Lead the Commission Cycle</strong>: From validating new deals in Salesforce to calculating and issuing accurate commission payments, you’ll manage the full process and ensure timely, transparent communication with reps.</li>
 <li><strong>Ensure Data Accuracy: </strong>Audit and reconcile commission payouts to match plan policies. Identify errors and resolve discrepancies before they impact trust or reporting.</li>
 <li><strong>Drive Process Improvement: </strong>Identify opportunities to automate and streamline workflows using tools like Adaptive Insights, ICM, or even AI innovations in Finance.</li>
 <li><strong>Support FP&amp;A Initiatives: </strong>Assist with budgeting, forecasting, and variance analysis. Provide insights into commission expenses and related revenue or ARR trends.</li>
 <li><strong>Partner Cross-Functionally: </strong>Collaborate daily with Sales, RevOps, Accounting, and Finance to ensure alignment and maintain clean, actionable data.</li>
 <li><strong>Shape Compensation Strategy: </strong>Contribute insights to help evolve commission structures that reinforce business goals and high-performance behaviors.<br><br></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Compensation</strong></p>
<p>We are committed to fair and equitable compensation practices.<br>
 The total pay range for this role is $50,000 - $75,000.<br>
 Actual compensation packages are based on several factors that are unique to each candidate, including but not limited to: skill set, depth of experience, certifications, and specific work location.</p>
