INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (56, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/sensei/jobs/48579586-cfo#content', 'CFO', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/sensei?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkFjY291bnRpbmclMjAlMjYlMjBGaW5hbmNlIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/e4e52b25-bb2e-5f54-8c4d-c24c92cacc24-1748914292', 'Sensei', 'Accounting & Finance', 1744070400, '<div>
 <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>About Sensei:</strong></b><span> Sensei is revolutionising the retail and technology sectors with innovative solutions. We\'ve built the technology to digitise physical stores and power them with the most advanced AI and computer-vision technology in a reliable, cost-effective, and privacy-driven platform to enhance the retail business and build the best shopping experience!</span></p>
 <p dir="ltr"><span>We work with some of the best retailers and distinguish ourselves by creating a technology that welcomes all buyers, using all forms of payment with real-time baskets.</span></p>
 <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>About Your Team</strong></b><span> As Sensei’s CFO, you\'ll join our executive leadership team, which works closely with the CEO and executives across growth, operations, engineering, and product. You will lead the finance team, playing a pivotal role in shaping our fast-growing startup\'s financial strategy and operational excellence.</span></p>
 <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>How Can You Help?</strong></b><span> As CFO, you will establish and lead financial processes, systems, and controls that drive transparency and strategic decision-making. Your expertise will enhance our financial rigor, ensuring profitability, growth, and sustained investor confidence. Your role will include managing fundraising initiatives, pricing strategy, budgeting, and investor relations.</span></p>
 <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>Daily at Sensei, you will:</strong></b></p>
 <ul>
  <li value="1"><span>Enable the fundraising process, preparing compelling investment memos and growth projections to support Sensei’s growth acceleration and strategic alliances.</span></li>
  <li value="2"><span>Provide strategic financial vision, partnering closely with the CEO and senior leadership.</span></li>
  <li value="3"><span>Implement, automate and manage financial processes and systems that accurately capture revenues, expenses, and operational metrics (e.g., CAC, service margin), enabling precise and immediate visibility into financial performance.</span></li>
  <li value="4"><span>Prepare and deliver insightful monthly and quarterly investor materials, strategically communicating financial performance, aligning expectations, and strengthening investor relations.</span></li>
  <li value="5"><span>Collaborate with the Growth team to develop annual budgets, sales targets, and incentive plans aligned with company objectives.</span></li>
  <li value="6"><span>Provide strategic input on M&amp;A opportunities, infrastructure funds, and financing lines to support Sensei’s growth and acceleration.</span></li>
  <li value="7"><span>Collaborate with our Financial Director on cash management, internal controls, compliance, audit, tax, treasury, planning, and analysis.</span></li>
  <li value="8"><span>Centralise pricing logic and approval of customer proposals, ensuring profitability and aligning commercial decisions with strategic goals.</span></li>
 </ul>
 <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>You Will Bring to the Table:</strong></b></p>
 <ul>
  <li value="1"><span>Proven track record as CFO or senior finance executive, ideally within high-growth startups or technology-driven businesses.</span></li>
  <li value="2"><span>Demonstrable experience implementing financial systems and processes that enhance transparency, control, and strategic decision-making.</span></li>
  <li value="3"><span>Strong expertise in financial metrics, pricing strategy, profitability analysis, and proposal validation frameworks.</span></li>
  <li value="4"><span>Excellent communication, negotiation, and presentation skills, with experience crafting investor relations materials, investment memos, and strategic communications.</span></li>
  <li value="5"><span>Hands-on experience in fundraising, investor management, and financial modeling for growth projections.</span></li>
  <li value="6"><span>Comfort guiding and participating in C-suite-level decisions and strategic discussions.</span></li>
  <li value="7"><span>Highly valued experience in M&amp;A, infrastructure funds, and financing strategies, complementing the executive team\'s capabilities.</span></li>
 </ul>
 <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>After Six Months, Success Means:</strong></b></p>
 <ul>
  <li value="1"><span>You have successfully implemented financial processes and tools, delivering complete visibility over revenues, expenses, and key metrics.</span></li>
  <li value="2"><span>Pricing logic and proposal approvals are centralised, ensuring every commercial decision is profitable and strategically aligned.</span></li>
  <li value="3"><span>Investor relations are strengthened through proactive, strategic communication of financial performance, enhancing investor confidence.</span></li>
  <li value="4"><span>You have led the preparation of fundraising materials, positioning Sensei for a successful investment round.</span></li>
  <li value="5"><span>An effective annual budgeting and sales incentive strategy has been established and adopted across relevant teams.</span></li>
  <li value="6"><span>You have contributed strategically to growth initiatives through insights on M&amp;A opportunities and financing strategies.</span></li>
 </ul>
 <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>What\'s in it for You:</strong></b></p>
 <ul>
  <li value="1"><span>Collaborate with outstanding people, enhance your skill set, and make a meaningful contribution to the world</span></li>
  <li value="2"><span>Competitive salary</span></li>
  <li value="3"><span>Relevant Stock Options</span></li>
  <li value="4"><span>Meal card</span></li>
  <li value="5"><span>Flexible benefits package, be it a gym membership, the monthly fee of your child’s kindergarten, or an investment for retirement – the choice is yours!</span></li>
  <li value="6"><span>Health Insurance</span></li>
  <li value="7"><span>Hybrid Working Model</span></li>
  <li value="8"><span>5 extra days off per year on top of 22 statutory leave days: Your Birthday, Carnival Day, Christmas Eve, and 2 Health-Focus Days</span></li>
  <li value="9"><span>Opportunity to shape financial strategy and contribute significantly to Sensei’s rapid growth and market impact.</span></li>
 </ul>
 <div>
 </div>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (57, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline/jobs/48334584-head-of-finance-africa#content', 'Head of Finance, Africa', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkFjY291bnRpbmclMjAlMjYlMjBGaW5hbmNlIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/716c870c-b07d-50ff-ab75-427af872bf20-1740432205', 'Zipline', 'Accounting & Finance', 1743638400, '<h3><strong>About Zipline</strong></h3>
<div>
 <p>Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building, manufacturing and operating the first instant delivery and logistics system that serves all humans equally, wherever they are. From powering Rwanda’s national blood delivery network and Ghana’s COVID-19 vaccine distribution, to providing on-demand home delivery for Walmart, to enabling healthcare providers to bring care directly to U.S. homes, we are transforming the way things move for businesses, governments and consumers. The technology is complex but the idea is simple: a teleportation service that delivers what you need, when you need it. Through our technology that includes robotics and autonomy, we are decarbonizing delivery, decreasing road congestion, and reducing fossil fuel consumption and air pollution, while providing equitable access to billions of people and building a more resilient global supply chain.</p><span>Join Zipline and help us to make good on our promise to build an equitable and more resilient global supply chain for billions of people</span><span>.</span>
</div>
<div>
 <h3><strong>About You and The Role </strong></h3>
 <p>As <strong>Head of Finance for Zipline Africa</strong>, you will be a core member of Zipline’s <strong>Africa Leadership Team</strong>, responsible for driving financial strategy, operational efficiency, and growth initiatives across our Africa operations. Reporting into our <strong>US-based Global Head of Finance</strong>, you will work closely with our <strong>local finance and accounting teams</strong> to ensure Zipline’s financial health and scalability across multiple African markets.</p>
 <p>This role requires a <strong>seasoned finance leader with international experience</strong> and expertise in managing the financial complexities of scaling a high-growth, operations-intensive business. You will be instrumental in <strong>developing strategic analyses to enhance profitability and scalability</strong> for <strong>Zipline’s Platform 1 business in Africa</strong>.</p>
 <h3>What You\'ll Do</h3>
 <h4><strong>Financial Strategy &amp; Leadership</strong></h4>
 <ul>
  <li>Act as a <strong>strategic partner</strong> to Zipline’s <strong>Africa leadership team</strong>, advising on financial planning, investment decisions, and business growth initiatives.</li>
  <li>Lead <strong>financial forecasting, budgeting, and performance analysis</strong> to optimize financial resources and ensure the sustainability of Zipline’s Africa operations.</li>
  <li>Identify and implement <strong>cost-saving and efficiency strategies</strong> to improve profitability while maintaining operational excellence.</li>
  <li>Develop <strong>long-term financial models</strong> to assess different market strategies and guide expansion efforts.</li>
 </ul>
 <h4><strong>Accounting &amp; Compliance</strong></h4>
 <ul>
  <li>Partner with <strong>local accounting teams</strong> to improve financial reporting accuracy, streamline processes, and ensure timely financial close cycles.</li>
  <li>Work with Zipline’s <strong>US-based finance leadership</strong> to standardize financial practices across global operations.</li>
  <li>Participate in <strong>audit processes</strong> and liaise with regulatory bodies to ensure transparency and compliance.</li>
  <li>Coordinate with local and US-based Tax advisors to ensure Tax compliance across entities</li>
 </ul>
 <h4><strong>Operational Finance &amp; Business Partnering</strong></h4>
 <ul>
  <li>Serve as a <strong>financial thought leader</strong> for Zipline’s operations in Africa, helping local teams navigate financial complexities and drive sustainable growth.</li>
  <li>Partner with <strong>engineering, supply chain, logistics, and deployment teams</strong> to ensure cost-effective operations and strong unit economics.</li>
  <li>Work closely with <strong>government, donor and commercial partners</strong> to structure financially viable contracts and partnerships.</li>
 </ul>
 <h4><strong>Scaling &amp; Profitability of Zipline’s Business</strong></h4>
 <ul>
  <li>Conduct <strong>strategic financial analysis</strong> to enhance the scalability and profitability of Zipline’s Platform 1 operations in Africa.</li>
  <li>Develop insights into <strong>market expansion opportunities, pricing strategies, and operational efficiencies</strong> to drive sustainable business growth.</li>
  <li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to assess the <strong>financial feasibility of launching new products and services</strong> in Africa.</li>
  <li>Develop roadmaps and strategies for Zipline to launch <strong>Platform 2 </strong>in Africa</li>
 </ul>
 <h3>What You\'ll Bring</h3>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>8+ years of experience in finance</strong>, including <strong>2+ years in a financial leadership role</strong> within a multinational or high-growth company.</li>
  <li>Knowledge of accounting principals and direct experience working with <strong>IFRS and local accounting regulations</strong> in African markets.</li>
  <li>Experience managing <strong>financial operations for an international company with African market exposure</strong>.</li>
  <li>Proven ability to <strong>partner with in-country finance and accounting teams</strong> while partnering with global finance leadership.</li>
  <li>Excellent <strong>financial modeling, forecasting, and strategic analysis</strong> skills.</li>
  <li>Experience working with <strong>operations-heavy businesses</strong> (e.g., supply chain, logistics, or manufacturing).</li>
  <li>Ability to <strong>influence executive stakeholders</strong> and work cross-functionally across finance, operations, and commercial teams.</li>
  <li>Strong <strong>communication and leadership skills</strong>, with the ability to operate in fast-paced and evolving markets.</li>
 </ul>
 <h3>What Else You Need to Know</h3>
 <div>
  <div>
   Zipline is an equal opportunity employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, ancestry, national origin, religion or religious creed, mental or physical disability, medical condition, genetic information, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, and related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital status, military or veteran status, citizenship, or other characteristics protected by state, federal or local law or our other policies.
  </div>
  <div>
  </div>
  <div>
   We value diversity at Zipline and welcome applications from those who are traditionally underrepresented in tech. If you like the sound of this position but are not sure if you are the perfect fit, please apply!
  </div>
  <div>
  </div>
  <div>
   --
  </div>
  <div>
   <h3><strong>Please Note</strong></h3>
   <p><span>We have received reports stating that certain individuals are reaching out to people under false pretenses, claiming to be Zipline employees, affiliates, agents, or representatives. They may seek to gain access to your personal information or to acquire money from you by offering fictitious employment opportunities or by claiming that they are contacting you on Zipline’s behalf.</span></p>
   <p><span>Genuine Zipline employees or representatives will never ask you for money or payment in exchange for employment opportunities or other related services. Any such offer of employment or any other service in exchange for fees that claims to be from us is deceitful and part of a fraud.</span></p>
   <p><span>If you believe you have been targeted by a fraudulent party, we ask that you immediately get in touch with us via email at</span><strong> security@flyzipline.com</strong><span> upon receiving a suspicious offer or claim.</span></p>
  </div>
 </div>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (58, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/preply/jobs/47969725-finance-operations-lead#content', 'Finance Operations Lead', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/preply?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkFjY291bnRpbmclMjAlMjYlMjBGaW5hbmNlIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/bd8a3585-967c-5c75-b55d-2fe6d8e2962c-1749087038', 'Preply', 'Accounting & Finance', 1743033600, '<h3>We power people\'s progress.</h3>
<p>At Preply, we’re all about creating life-changing learning experiences. We help people discover the magic of the perfect tutor, craft a personalized learning journey, and stay motivated to keep growing. Our approach is human-led, tech-enabled - and it’s creating real impact. So far, 90,000 tutors have delivered over 20 million lessons to learners in more than 175 countries. Every Preply lesson sparks change, fuels ambition, and drives progress that matters.</p>
<h3>Meet the team!</h3>
<p>At Preply, Finance Operations plays a crucial role in ensuring our financial data is accurate, scalable, and seamlessly integrated across all business functions. As we grow, the complexity of our revenue streams, payment processing, and financial reporting presents exciting challenges that require automation, innovation, and strong cross-functional collaboration.</p>
<p>As part of the Finance Operations team, you’ll work at the intersection of finance, data, and technology, helping to streamline financial processes, improve integrations, and ensure consistency in financial reporting. You’ll collaborate closely with Accounting, FP&amp;A, Data, People, and B2B teams to optimize workflows, enhance automation, and drive improvements in financial accuracy. Your contributions will help Preply scale efficiently, maintain financial integrity, and create a seamless financial experience across teams and systems.</p>
<p>Our Finance team is focused on building a best-in-class financial ecosystem that empowers data-driven decisions and operational efficiency as we scale to the next level.</p>
<h3>What you’ll be doing:</h3>
<ul>
 <li>Oversee and enhance the finance tech stack, ensuring smooth integrations between systems (Netsuite, Abacum, etc.).</li>
 <li>Manage and optimize existing financial integrations, identifying gaps and ensuring consistency in data flows across revenue, cash, and reporting.</li>
 <li>Ensure consistency and accuracy in financial reporting, reconciling data across different sources to prevent discrepancies.</li>
 <li>Partner with Accounting, FP&amp;A, and Data teams to align on data definitions, financial reporting accuracy, and automation initiatives.</li>
 <li>Own monthly &amp; quarterly consolidated management reporting including Budget vs Actuals analyses, dashboards, and Board materials. Coordinate across relevant teams to surface insights to leadership.</li>
 <li>Lead finance automation projects, reducing manual work and improving efficiency across finance-related processes.</li>
 <li>Work closely with Product teams to improve our Payments’ stack and deliver business value via reduced payment fees, new currencies, payment methods, and more</li>
 <li>Work closely with People and B2B teams to improve financial workflows, including payroll, billing, and revenue recognition.</li>
 <li>Collaborate on cross-functional finance projects, driving process improvements and ensuring seamless execution.</li>
 <li>Act as the project manager for finance operations, keeping stakeholders informed, tracking milestones, and ensuring timely completion of key initiatives.</li>
 <li>Be a problem-solver and enabler, ensuring finance is an efficient, data-driven, and user-friendly function across the organization.</li>
</ul>
<h3>What you need to succeed:</h3>
<ul>
 <li>+5 years’ experience in a Finance Operations role, ideally for a Tech company with around 1,000+ employees or similar size</li>
 <li>Strong finance systems expertise, with experience in ERP systems, planning tools, payment platforms, and financial reporting tools. SQL knowledge is a plus.</li>
 <li>Solid understanding of financial data structures, US GAAP, revenue recognition, and cash reconciliation.</li>
 <li>Experience managing integrations between finance and other business systems (e.g., CRM, HR, payments).</li>
 <li>Strong analytical skills, with the ability to troubleshoot discrepancies and ensure data consistency.</li>
 <li>Excellent collaboration skills, working effectively with Accounting, FP&amp;A, Data, and cross-functional teams.</li>
 <li>Project management experience, with the ability to drive initiatives from scoping to execution.</li>
 <li>Automation mindset, comfortable leveraging technology to improve finance processes.</li>
 <li>Proactive and solution-oriented, able to work independently and adapt in a fast-paced environment.</li>
 <li>Great communication skills, making finance processes easy to understand and work with across teams.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Why you’ll love it at Preply:</h3>
<ul>
 <li>Open, collaborative, dynamic and diverse culture</li>
 <li>Generous monthly allowance for lessons on <a href="http://preply.coma/">Preply.com</a></li>
 <li>Learning &amp; Development budget, including time off for your self-development</li>
 <li>Competitive financial package with equity, leave allowance and health insurance</li>
 <li>Access to free mental health support platforms</li>
 <li>Not in Barcelona? We offer an attractive relocation package to join us in our Preply Barcelona Hub</li>
 <li>Access to Gympass-partnered wellness and gym centers throughout Spain to promote and support well-being and physical health;</li>
 <li>Opportunity to shape the lives of learners and tutors from over 175 countries through language learning and teaching</li>
</ul>
<h3>Our Principles</h3>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Care to change the world</strong> - We are passionate about our work and care deeply about its impact to be life changing.</li>
 <li><strong>We do it for learners</strong> - For both Preply and tutors, learners are why we do what we do. Every day we focus on empowering tutors to deliver an exceptional learning experience.</li>
 <li><strong>Keep perfecting</strong> - To create an outstanding customer experience, we focus on simplicity, smoothness, and enjoyment, continually perfecting it as every detail matters.</li>
 <li><strong>Now is the time</strong> - In a fast-paced world, it matters how quickly we act. Now is the time to make great things happen.</li>
 <li><strong>Disciplined execution</strong> - What makes us disciplined is the excellence in our execution. We set clear goals, focus on what matters, and utilize our resources efficiently.</li>
 <li><strong>Dive deep</strong> - We leverage business acumen and curiosity to investigate disparities between numbers and stories, unlocking meaningful insights to guide our decisions.</li>
 <li><strong>Growth mindset </strong>- We proactively seek growth opportunities and believe today\'s best performance becomes tomorrow\'s starting point. We humbly embrace feedback and learn from setbacks.</li>
 <li><strong>Raise the bar</strong> - We raise our performance standards continuously, alongside each new hire and promotion. We build diverse and high-performing teams that can make a real difference.</li>
 <li><strong>Challenge, disagree and commit</strong> - We value open and candid communication, even when we don’t fully agree. We speak our minds, challenge when necessary, and fully commit to decisions once made.</li>
 <li><strong>One Preply</strong> - We prioritize collaboration, inclusion, and the success of our team over personal ambitions. Together, we support and celebrate each other\'s progress.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion</h3>
<p>Preply is committed to creating a diverse and inclusive environment where people from all backgrounds can thrive. Different opinions and viewpoints are key ingredients in our success as a multicultural Ed-Tech company.</p>
<p>Preply will consider all applications for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, disability, age or veteran status. Together, we are The World Class.</p>
<p>#LI-BV1</p>');
