<p><strong>Experience &amp; Skills</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>2+ years in an instructional design, L&amp;D, or training specialist role, preferably within customer support or operations.</li>
 <li>Proven experience in designing asynchronous learning content for adult learners using instructional design frameworks (e.g., ADDIE, SAM).</li>
 <li>Strong working knowledge of e-learning authoring tools (e.g., Articulate, Rise, Captivate, Canva, or similar).</li>
 <li>Experience in maintaining knowledge bases and/or building structured learning pathways in LMS platforms.</li>
 <li>Strong written communication skills with a flair for turning complexity into simplicity.</li>
 <li>Comfortable analyzing performance data and drawing insights to shape training strategy.</li>
 <li>Collaborative mindset and experience working with cross-functional stakeholders (e.g., QA, WFM, Product, Ops).</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Nice to have</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Background in Customer Support operations, especially within a digital or fast-paced environment.</li>
 <li>Experience with remote facilitation and delivering training in international and multicultural teams.</li>
 <li>Familiarity with multimedia content creation (basic video editing, visual design, or audio narration).</li>
 <li>Proficiency in additional languages (especially Spanish or Ukrainian).</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Why you’ll love it at Preply:</strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>An open, collaborative, dynamic and diverse culture;</li>
 <li>A generous monthly allowance for lessons on<a href="http://preply.com/"> Preply.com</a>, Learning &amp; Development budget and time off for your self-development;</li>
