 <li>12+ million DataCamp learners</li>
 <li>And a global learning community spread across 180+ countries.</li>
</ul>
<p>At DataCamp, we believe that everyone deserves access to high-quality education and data and AI skill development for a more secure future. From our first-class courses, projects, code-alongs, certification programs, and DataLab—we are an all-in-one platform on a mission to democratize data and AI education for all.</p>
<h2><span><strong>About the Role</strong></span></h2>
<p>As a Senior Marketing Analyst at DataCamp, you will play a pivotal role in driving our paid marketing strategy through data-driven insights. Reporting to the Marketing Analytics Manager, you\'ll be deeply involved in data quality assurance, marketing channel reporting, LTV estimation, marketing mix modeling, and incrementality testing. Your work will directly influence our marketing decisions and strategies, enhancing our reach and effectiveness.</p>
<p>You will influence changes by bringing data to the table, and promoting data-driven development and decision-making. To be successful you will need to collaborate with a strong team of marketing leaders, data scientists, data engineers and software engineers. You will get to do all of this while leveraging DataCamp\'s rich data and state-of-the-art data science infrastructure.</p>
<p>In pursuing DataCamp’s mission an AI-first company, you will engage with exciting new technologies and push the boundaries of what a data analyst can do.</p>
<p><span><strong>Responsibilities</strong></span></p>
