INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (158, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/healthie/jobs/51763933-technical-product-manager#content', 'Technical Product Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/healthie?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIklUIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/c458b2e9-355d-5d7a-a524-701a5756dcce-1748914164', 'Healthie', 'IT', 1748563200, '<p><strong>* This is a Hybrid position working 3x per week in our NYC HQ, you must be located in NYC and open to working 3 days/week in person.</strong></p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Our mission</strong></p>
<p>Healthie powers virtual-first care delivery while improving access to healthcare and enabling better healthcare outcomes through technology.</p>
<p>We build infrastructure that all healthcare organizations need to perform virtual-first care. Between our EHR, scheduling, and patient engagement solutions, Healthie’s API-first approach makes it easy for organizations of every size to build, customize, and scale their business.</p>
<p>Today, we power thousands of organizations—ranging from small private practices, to digital health startups and multi-billion-dollar healthcare companies. Leveraging Healthie, our customers deliver care to millions of patients, across the full spectrum of healthcare service—from preventative health and wellness to complex chronic care management.</p>
<p>We believe that the future of healthcare delivery is virtual-first, longitudinal, and collaborative. Learn more at: <a href="https://www.gethealthie.com/">https://www.gethealthie.com/</a></p>
<hr>
<p>We’re looking for an experienced <strong>Technical Product Manager - Data Products</strong> at Healthie to accelerate the growth of our data product offerings. This role presents a unique opportunity to collaborate with cross-functional teams to define and prioritize data initiatives, ensuring the effective scaling of our data ecosystem. You\'ll play a key role in crafting and executing Healthie’s Data Products Roadmap for internal and external customers as well as working to drive the quality of data products and pipelines that empower critical business insights for Healthie and our customers.</p>
<h3><strong>About the role</strong></h3>
<p>The <strong>Technical Product Manager - Data Products</strong> will focus on managing the data team’s product strategy, which includes overseeing ETL workflows, data pipelines, and the development of our data lake and analytics products for internal and external customers. You’ll work closely with engineering, business units, and external stakeholders to translate user needs into technical requirements, ensuring alignment between data initiatives and business objectives. You will be responsible for launching multiple new products as well as overseeing iterative development over the product life cycle.</p>
<p>This is the ideal role for someone passionate about data solutions, eager to facilitate collaboration across teams, and excited to help build a robust, scalable data infrastructure that drives business decisions. Our ideal candidate is technically savvy, a strong communicator, and dedicated to fostering data-driven decision-making throughout Healthie.</p>
<p><strong>Details</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>This is a full-time, hybrid position based in our NYC HQ</li>
 <li>The base salary for this role is $160,000-$180,000 per year.</li>
 <li>U.S. work authorization is required and Healthie does not provide sponsorship.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>About you</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>You have 3+ years of experience in product management, with at least 1 year focused on data and reporting products or a related field.</li>
 <li>Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to simplify complex technical concepts for diverse audiences.</li>
 <li>You have a proven ability to collaborate with cross-functional teams, ensuring alignment between business and technical requirements.</li>
 <li>You excel at translating business needs into technical solutions, managing data initiatives, and driving product strategy.</li>
 <li>You take ownership of managing data product roadmaps, prioritizing initiatives, and ensuring timely delivery of data solutions.</li>
 <li>You are passionate about identifying areas of opportunity to leverage data in building AI solutions that solve real problems for Healthie, our Providers, and their Patients.</li>
 <li>You are a strong problem-solver, able to break down complex technical challenges and find solutions that align with business objectives.</li>
 <li>Experience working with BI tools such as Metabase, Power BI, or Looker, and familiarity with ETL processes and data warehousing.</li>
 <li>Proficiency in SQL preferred.</li>
 <li>You thrive in agile environments, with a bias toward execution and a focus on delivering results through iterative product development.</li>
 <li>You are passionate about healthcare and improving patient outcomes through data-driven insights and solutions.</li>
</ul>
<h4><strong>Interview Process</strong></h4>
<ul>
 <li>Initial Screen with Debbie (20 minutes)</li>
 <li>Quick chat with Katie, Director of Talent (20 minutes)</li>
 <li>Interview with Max, Director of Product (30 minutes)</li>
 <li>Executive Interview with Cavan CTO, cofounder (20 minutes)</li>
 <li>Complete our Take Home Assessment (asynchronously)</li>
 <li>Review Take Home Assessment with: (30 minutes each) 
  <ul>
   <li>Ani &amp; Jae, Engineering</li>
   <li>Matt &amp; Rachel, Design &amp; Product</li>
  </ul></li>
 <li>Reference checks</li>
</ul>
<p>To learn more about Working at Healthie &amp; our benefits, <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Yg-gwmd6LORDskg-mOFBMBhrRH9n_JILvUvNLv-gG2w/edit?tab=t.0">click here</a>.</p>
<p><em>Healthie participates in e-verify</em></p>
<div>
 <p><em>Healthie is committed to equal employment opportunity. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to and will not be discriminated against based on age, race, gender, color, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, veteran status, disability or any other protected category. We\'re proud to be building a diverse and inclusive environment that encourages collaboration, creativity, and growth. Whatever your background, please apply if this is a role that would make you excited to come into work every day.<span> </span></em></p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (159, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/arrived-2/jobs/51706279-technical-operations-specialist#content', 'Technical Operations Specialist', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/arrived-2?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIklUIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/8244e6e0-f621-538f-837b-fdc0675c26cc-1750176380', 'Arrived', 'IT', 1748476800, '<div>
 <p><em>This position is only open to candidates located in the following states and/or markets: Arkansas, Arizona, California, Colorado, Illinois, Massachusetts, Michigan, Nevada, North Carolina, New Jersey, New York, Tennessee, Texas, Washington.</em></p>
 <h2><strong>What You Will Do</strong></h2>
 <p>You’ll join our<strong> Build for Scale team</strong>, which owns <strong>internal tooling, automation</strong>, and <strong>operational infrastructure</strong>. As our team’s second hire, you’ll focus on capturing raw data from a wide array of sources (both structured and unstructured), and transforming it into clean, reliable systems that <strong>power reporting, automation, and AI implementations</strong> across the company. You’ll serve as the connective tissue between subject-matter experts (Legal, Accounting, Investments), internal tools, and data — automating where possible, structuring where needed. You’ll ship internal products quickly, <strong>balancing speed and scalability</strong>, all so the rest of the company can move faster and be more effective.</p>
 <h2><strong>How You Will Contribute</strong></h2>
 <p><strong>You will:</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>Run end-to-end process-improvement projects</strong> – map processes, identify optimization opportunities, and deliver solutions that improve efficiency and effectiveness of teams.</li>
  <li><strong>Partner cross-functionally &amp; triage requests</strong> – act as the connector between Legal, Finance, Investments, Product, and Engineering teams, gathering requirements and scoping solutions that work for all stakeholders.</li>
  <li><strong>Create internal tooling &amp; automations</strong> – build and maintain low-code apps, scripts, and integrations that eliminate manual work and streamline repeatable operational tasks (using tools like Coda, Zapier, n8n, Python scripts).</li>
  <li><strong>Enable self-service analytics &amp; reporting</strong> – work with internal teams to define business-critical metrics and help guide the building of dashboards, reports, and ad-hoc analyses to surface accurate, actionable insights.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>And ideally be able to:</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>Build scalable data infrastructure &amp; pipelines</strong> – design, implement, and maintain lightweight ETLs that consolidate data from Salesforce, Coda, internal databases, external APIs, and other tools so information flows reliably as the business grows (using tools like Snowflake and Fivetran).</li>
  <li><strong>Model, monitor, and assure data quality</strong> – turn raw inputs into clean semantic layers and data marts, establish QA processes and documentation, and help create an agreed upon “single source of truth” for internal teams.</li>
  <li><strong>Own system integrations &amp; maintenance</strong> – keep data pipelines and operational systems healthy; debug workflows and data connections when they break.</li>
  <li><strong>Lay the foundation for future scalability</strong> – incrementally add structure, content, and best practices so that our systems scale into the future, and so that Product and Engineering teams can easily build robust internal tools on top of our infrastructure.</li>
 </ul>
 <h2><strong>What Makes a Great Fit</strong></h2>
 <p><strong>Having all traits/experience is </strong><strong><em>not necessary</em></strong><strong> – there are many ways to be valuable in this role.</strong></p>
 <p>You have <strong>2–5</strong> years of experience in any of:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Engineering (software, data, infrastructure)</li>
  <li>Technical Operations (systems, automation)</li>
  <li>Operations at a tech company</li>
  <li>Data Science</li>
 </ul>
 <h3><strong>Semi-Technical Builder</strong></h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Experience with no-code/low-code tools (Zapier, Retool, Coda, n8n, etc)</li>
  <li>Know when and software engineer, but can write/debug a solid Python script with the help of AI</li>
  <li>Comfortable building functional MVPs: shipping fast, iterating, and improving over time</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Comfortable with Data</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Strong with data: fluent in <strong>SQL</strong>, wrangling spreadsheets, and logic. Can answer critical business questions using data in a way that builds trust and understand business levers well enough to interpret data and make recommendations</li>
  <li>Have set up <strong>ETLs</strong> using tools like dbt, Airbyte, Fivetran, or custom scripts</li>
  <li>Understand API basics (GET/POST, JSON formats), and have hands-on experience working with <strong>APIs</strong>, webhooks, and lightweight scripting for integrations</li>
  <li>Know how to design <strong>semantic layers</strong> and define clean, well-modeled data marts</li>
  <li>Constantly bringing structure to everything</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Systems Thinker &amp; Workflow Oriented</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Can take a vague business process and turn it into a repeatable workflow</li>
  <li>Naturally reduce friction – by automating, documenting, or improving handoffs</li>
  <li>Always looking for a way to reduce manual error and inefficiency</li>
  <li>Motivated by building systems that create output — not just dashboards that track results</li>
 </ul>
 <h3><strong>Project Management &amp; Collaboration</strong></h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Cross-functional experience – can talk to Legal, Finance, Investments, and Product, and translate between them</li>
  <li>Comfortable running small projects, following up on dependencies, and closing loops</li>
  <li>Have strong project ownership skills: you see things through from start to finish</li>
  <li>Communicate clearly with both technical and non-technical stakeholders, and translate business needs into structured data solutions</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong><br></strong><strong>Why Arrived?</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>Culture</strong>: We’re a growing team, passionate about our mission to help others meet their financial goals. You’ll have the opportunity to put your stamp on Arrived from the beginning.</li>
  <li><strong>Growth</strong>: We’re solving tough problems and we’re moving at a fast pace. Arrived is creating something completely new and we’re looking for team members who can be as excited about Arrived as we are.</li>
  <li><strong>Benefits</strong>: We offer competitive salary &amp; equity compensation. A flexible PTO policy to allow our team to take time away whenever they need. And employer sponsored Health, Dental, and Vision plans.</li>
  <li><strong>Perks</strong>: Every Arrived employee gets a monthly cash bonus to invest in Arrived properties so that they can start building passive income (we only ask that you don\'t quit your job and leave us high and dry when you’re swimming in dividends). 😊</li>
  <li><strong>Location</strong>: Arrived is a remote-first company headquartered in Seattle, WA.</li>
 </ul>
 <p>*<em>If you’ve made it down this far and are even more excited than you were 5 minutes ago, please apply or reach out to us for more information. Thanks for your time and let us know when you’ve Arrived.*</em></p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (160, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/novo-space/jobs/51697266-space-hardware-manufacturing-test-specialist#content', 'Space Hardware Manufacturing & Test Specialist', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/novo-space?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIklUIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/b6525d23-43d0-531d-a99a-f223de376259-1747532197', 'Novo Space', 'IT', 1748476800, '<p><span><span><span>Novo Space</span> is a vibrant startup developing high-performance, radiation-tolerant computers to support the growing need for autonomous systems, machine learning in space and other data-intensive processing technologies. The products we build together will be at the heart of future weather forecasting, geolocation, earth observation, and communication satellites, and will help humankind improve life on this planet and conquer other planets in our solar system. </span><span> </span></span></p>
<p><span><span>Space Hardware Manufacturing &amp; Test Specialist</span><span> </span></span></p>
<p><span><span>About the Position</span><span> </span></span></p>
<p><span><span>The Space Hardware Manufacturing &amp; Test Specialist will be responsible for the assembly, testing, and quality assurance of high-reliability electronic and mechanical components used in space applications. The ideal candidate combines hands-on technical expertise with strong attention to detail and a commitment to aerospace-grade quality. This role demands the ability to interpret complex engineering documentation and perform both functional and environmental testing to validate product performance under extreme conditions.</span><span> </span></span></p>
<p><span><span>Location</span><span>: Orlando, FL</span><span> </span></span></p>
<p><span><span>Key responsibilities:</span><span> </span></span></p>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Execute and optimize assembly processes for space-grade electronic and mechanical components, ensuring compliance with aerospace quality standards (e.g., IPC-A-610, J-STD-001, ECSS).</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Interpret engineering drawings, BOMs, and work instructions to accurately build, inspect, and troubleshoot products throughout the production cycle.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Support production readiness and continuous improvement initiatives, including tooling setup, process documentation, and feedback to design teams for manufacturability.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Execute functional and environmental tests on electronic and mechanical assemblies, ensuring conformance to space-grade performance and reliability requirements (e.g., thermal cycling, vibration, electrical validation).</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Support root cause analysis and corrective actions for production issues, working closely with engineering and manufacturing teams to resolve non-conformances.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Ensure traceability and quality records, ensuring all manufacturing steps are documented in accordance with internal procedures and product compliance. Manage test data, calibration records, and quality control metrics throughout the production lifecycle.</span><span> </span></span><span><br></span></li>
</ul>
<p><span><span>REQUIRED education, work experience, knowledge/skills:</span><span> </span></span></p>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Understanding of IPC standard</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Experience: 3+ years in manufacturing and testing of electronic systems.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Cable &amp; Harness Assembly: Experience in crimping, soldering and wire stripping.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Testing Knowledge: Familiarity with functional and environmental testing (e.g., vibration, thermal cycling, electrical test protocols).</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Documentation &amp; Traceability: Strong command of documentation control, traceability practices, and use of digital quality systems.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Reading &amp; Interpretation: Proficient in reading and interpreting engineering drawings, BOMs, PCB Layouts or gerbers, and work instructions.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Tools &amp; Instrumentation: Skilled in using soldering equipment, microscopes, multimeters, oscilloscopes, and thermal chambers.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Problem Solving: Capable of supporting root cause investigations and implementing corrective actions in a production environment.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span><span>Communication: Able to clearly document and communicate findings and contribute effectively to cross-functional teams.</span><span> </span></span></li>
</ul>
