 <li><span>This is a unique opportunity for someone who thrives in a fast-paced, startup-like environment within an established and mission-driven company.</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span><strong><br><br>
   Why you\'ll love the role: </strong></span></p>
<ul>
 <li><span><strong>Video Editing</strong>: Cut and assemble video content from scratch, combining live action, animation, stock, VO, and music to deliver highly engaging, polished videos for classroom use.</span></li>
 <li><span><strong>Basic Animation &amp; Motion Graphics</strong>: Create light animation, kinetic text, and visual effects using tools like After Effects.</span></li>
 <li><span><strong>Graphic Design Support</strong>: Edit and format assets in Photoshop and Illustrator, including thumbnails, title cards, storyboards, style frames, and other visual collateral.</span></li>
 <li><span><strong>Shoot Direction &amp; Support</strong>: Assist in planning, directing, and capturing professional video and audio sessions (VO, talent shoots, interviews, music recording).</span></li>
 <li><span><strong>Project Management</strong>: Help manage production timelines, coordinate with freelance editors, illustrators, and animators, and track assets through delivery.</span></li>
 <li><span><strong>Creative Collaboration</strong>: Work closely with writers, musicians, illustrators, and internal subject matter experts to align visuals with educational goals and brand tone.</span></li>
 <li><span><strong>Studio Building</strong>: Support the development of workflows, asset libraries, studio gear selection, and onboarding new collaborators as the team grows.</span><br><br></li>
</ul>
<h3><span><strong>Who we\'re looking for:</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
 <li><span>A <strong>creative problem-solver</strong> with strong editing chops and a passion for visual storytelling.</span></li>
 <li><span>A <strong>multimedia generalist</strong> who’s comfortable jumping between video, animation, design, and production planning.</span></li>
 <li><span>A <strong>great communicator and collaborator</strong> who can work closely with artists, educators, and producers—and provide clear feedback to freelancers.</span></li>
 <li><span>Comfortable both <strong>on set and in the edit bay</strong>, with a strong sense of pacing, visual flow, and audience needs (especially K–12 learners).</span></li>
 <li><span><strong>Organized and proactive</strong>, with strong attention to detail and ability to manage shifting priorities.</span><br><br></li>
</ul>
<h3><span><strong>Why you\'re a great fit:</strong></span></h3>
<ul>
 <li><span><strong>3–6 years of experience</strong> in multimedia production (video editing, basic animation, content creation)</span></li>
 <li><span>You have experience in educational media, children’s content, or animation pipelines</span></li>
