 <h1></h1>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (192, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/localize/jobs/51822383-head-of-marketing-b2b-saas#content', 'Head of Marketing - B2B SaaS', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/localize?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk1hcmtldGluZyUyMCUyNiUyMENvbW11bmljYXRpb25zIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/0aeec5d0-f7cd-55bb-adbf-6d90f1fdc8a1-1748310151', 'Localize', 'Marketing & Communications', 1748649600, '<div>
 <p><a href="https://localizejs.com/"><strong>Localize</strong></a> is seeking a strategic, hands-on Head of Marketing to lead, manage, and scale our fully remote marketing team of 2–3 marketers. Reporting directly to the CEO, you’ll own the development of marketing strategy and oversee the execution of integrated campaigns spanning both inbound and outbound efforts. You will build a robust demand generation function that drives leads, accelerates pipeline, and supports the company’s ambitious revenue growth goals. This is an ideal role for a seasoned marketing professional with experience in B2B SaaS (annual contract values $30K–$100K) who can blend high-level strategy with hands-on project management and team leadership.</p>
 <p>Localize has achieved strong product-market fit and is now at a pivotal inflection point—ready to scale our marketing efforts aggressively and capture market demand for translation automation. As Head of Marketing, you’ll have the opportunity to shape the marketing function, from refining our already high-performing inbound channels to launching new outbound initiatives. You’ll work alongside an agile, cross-functional team to drive revenue growth, amplify brand presence, and solidify Localize’s position in the translation space. If you enjoy building marketing teams and driving results through repeatable, data-driven strategies, this role is for you.</p>
 <p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>
 <ol>
  <li><strong>Strategic Leadership &amp; Vision</strong>
   <ul>
    <li><strong>Strategic Planning &amp; Execution:</strong> Develop and implement comprehensive marketing strategies to strengthen our inbound marketing channels while developing and building out untapped channels such as outbound marketing, partnerships, and events.</li>
    <li><strong>Budget Ownership</strong>: Develop and manage the marketing budget, ensuring optimal allocation of resources and tracking ROI.</li>
    <li><strong>Scalable Demand Generation</strong>: Create repeatable, scalable, and data-driven demand generation processes to support company growth goals.</li>
    <li><strong>Multichannel Campaigns</strong>: Plan, develop, and execute marketing programs—including inbound (SEO, SEM, digital advertising, social media) and outbound (email, ABM, webinars, conferences)—to drive qualified leads from both new prospects and existing customers.</li>
    <li><strong>Targeted Messaging &amp; Buyer Journey</strong>: Align campaign messaging and content to specific audience segments, buyer profiles, and funnel stages.</li>
   </ul></li>
  <li><strong>Team Management &amp; Development</strong>
   <ul>
    <li><strong>Leadership &amp; Mentorship</strong>: Directly manage a remote team of 2–3 marketers, setting goals, providing feedback, and regularly evaluating performance.</li>
    <li><strong>Talent Growth</strong>: Identify skills gaps, recruit additional team members as needed, and utilize third-party agencies or contractors effectively.</li>
    <li><strong>Team Culture</strong>: Create an environment of collaboration, accountability, and professional development. Foster a culture of experimentation, iteration, and continuous improvement in all marketing initiatives.</li>
   </ul></li>
  <li><strong>Project Management &amp; Execution</strong>
   <ul>
    <li><strong>Project Oversight</strong>: Implement robust project management frameworks to ensure timely, within-budget delivery of campaigns and initiatives.</li>
    <li><strong>Milestone Tracking</strong>: Establish clear timelines, deliverables, and accountability structures for each campaign or project.</li>
    <li><strong>Cross-Functional Coordination</strong>: Coordinate with Sales, Customer Success, and Product teams to align marketing programs with company-wide objectives.</li>
   </ul></li>
  <li><strong>Demand Generation</strong>
   <ul>
    <li><strong>Inbound Optimization</strong>: Build on our existing success in organic search, paid advertising, and content marketing to expand reach and improve conversion rates.</li>
    <li><strong>Outbound Strategies</strong>: Collaborate closely with Sales to develop and execute outbound campaigns—such as ABM or targeted prospecting—that drive new business opportunities.</li>
    <li><strong>Campaign Development &amp; Launch</strong>: Oversee end-to-end planning and implementation of multi-channel marketing campaigns, adjusting tactics based on real-time data and feedback.</li>
   </ul></li>
  <li><strong>Analytics &amp; Reporting</strong>
   <ul>
    <li><strong>Data-Driven Decision Making</strong>: Define and monitor key performance indicators (KPIs) such as CAC, LTV, and conversion rates. Employ attribution models, media mix modeling, and funnel forecasting to optimize spend.</li>
    <li><strong>Performance Analysis</strong>: Provide regular reporting to executive leadership, offering actionable insights and strategic recommendations.</li>
    <li><strong>Market Intelligence</strong>: Stay current on industry trends, competitor activities, and emerging tools or platforms to keep Localize ahead of the market.</li>
   </ul></li>
 </ol>
 <p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>10+ years of B2B marketing experience</strong> (3+ in a leadership role), with a proven track record in both inbound and outbound demand generation.</li>
  <li><strong>SaaS &amp; Startup Experience</strong>: Demonstrated success marketing B2B SaaS solutions with annual contract values of $30K–$100K in a fast-paced, hands-on environment.</li>
  <li><strong>Team Leadership</strong>: Experience hiring, managing, and coaching high-performing marketing teams.</li>
  <li><strong>Project Management</strong>: Strong organizational skills and familiarity with project management methodologies or tools to keep teams and initiatives on track.</li>
  <li><strong>Technical Proficiency</strong>: Comfort with marketing automation (Hubspot preferred), SEO/SEM, PPC, email marketing, ABM, and analytics platforms.</li>
  <li><strong>Analytical &amp; Data-Driven</strong>: Capable of interpreting data to optimize campaigns, measure ROI, and guide strategy.</li>
  <li><strong>Outstanding Communication</strong>: Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to convey complex ideas succinctly and compellingly.</li>
  <li><strong>Collaboration &amp; Adaptability</strong>: Ability to thrive in a collaborative, fast-moving startup environment and pivot quickly based on evolving business needs.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Benefits &amp; Perks:</strong></p>
 <p>You’ll be joining a close knit and talented team, with plenty of opportunity for professional growth. We offer compensation + benefits that are on par with large companies, while also placing a high value on maintaining a healthy work-life balance.</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Competitive salary</li>
  <li>401(k) plan + 4% matching</li>
  <li>100% company-paid health, dental, and vision insurance</li>
  <li>Company-paid life insurance and AD&amp;D insurance</li>
  <li>We are 100% remote</li>
  <li>Shiny new Macbook Pro 16” (or computer of your choice)</li>
  <li>Monthly stipend for home internet costs</li>
  <li>Generous PTO package</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>About Localize</strong></p>
 <p>The Localize platform is used by <strong>700+ companies</strong> to automate the translation of their web and mobile applications and bring their products &amp; services to new markets at record speed. We help companies like<a href="https://ahrefs.com/"> Ahrefs</a> translate their website,<a href="https://nyulangone.org/"> NYU Langone Health</a> translate their urgent care scheduling page, and the<a href="https://www.unk.edu/"> University of Nebraska at Kearney</a> translate their international admissions page. To see our product in action, click any of those links and use the website’s language switcher to switch from English to another language.</p>
 <p>Localize works by providing a code snippet (similar to the Google Analytics JavaScript snippet) that our customers add to their website or web app. This snippet pulls content from the page into the Localize dashboard, where customers can add translations and manage their content. <strong>Localize automatically deploys those translations</strong> to the customer’s production site, reducing development costs and accelerating time to market.</p>
 <p>We are a fully remote team of <strong>~30 people</strong> offering competitive pay, a comprehensive benefits package, and a culture that emphasizes work-life balance.</p>
 <p><strong>How to Apply</strong></p>
 <p>Please send us your resume <strong>and a cover letter</strong> that showcases your personality and explains why you’re the right fit for this role. <strong>Previous experience working in a remote position is a must.</strong> We look forward to hearing from you!</p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (193, 'https://jobs.techstars.comhttps://vanhack.com/job/11397?utm_source=Techstars+job+board&utm_medium=getro.com&gh_src=Techstars+job+board', 'Intermediate Backend Engineer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/vanhack?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk1hcmtldGluZyUyMCUyNiUyMENvbW11bmljYXRpb25zIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/0908ecb7-238e-5c57-b010-b90918f3ddc5-1748828576', 'VanHack', 'Marketing & Communications', 1748563200, null);
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (194, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/sqor-io-2/jobs/51775741-co-founder-and-social-media-marketing-expert-equity-based-role#content', 'Co-Founder and Social Media Marketing Expert (**Equity-based role)', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/sqor-io-2?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk1hcmtldGluZyUyMCUyNiUyMENvbW11bmljYXRpb25zIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/8595ea82-e43a-5ffc-948c-a8b5f68f114e-1748880290', 'SQOR.io', 'Marketing & Communications', 1748563200, '<div>
 <p>United States-based applicants preferred.</p>
 <p>(** OPT is great. Minimum three years experience)</p>
 <p>Role: Social Media Marketing Expert – B2B SaaS</p>
 <p>Please Note:</p>
 <p>This role is for a hands-on, full-time, Social Media Marketing Expert with B2B SaaS marketing experience. The right candidate will actively create and execute daily social media activations <em>(HANDS ON)</em> across all social media platforms. This is a content-first, storytelling-driven role focused on earned engagement.This is NOT for paid ads, or for email lead-gen strategies.It is a direct engagement and content contributor role. This is a full-time, roll-up-your-sleeves position where you’ll be driving SQOR.ai’s brand presence, engagement, and thought leadership through social media and community interactions daily with all kinds of media: posts, videos, blopgs, community engagement, etc..About SQOR.ai</p>
 <p>SQOR.ai is the only plug-and-play AI platform that autonomously transforms SaaS data into real-time actionable intelligence. Designed for business leaders, investors, and consultants, SQOR.ai makes AI-driven decision intelligence effortless—no data teams, no infrastructure, no manual analytics.With over 500+ KPIs users can monitor and 60+ AI agents, SQOR.ai delivers causal insights, predictions, and real-time monitoring across sales, marketing, finance, customer success, operations, and product development.Our mission? To democratize access to decision intelligence, empowering all businesses to compete on a level playing field by unlocking insights without complexity, cost, or barriers.</p>
 <p>Watch our product video here: https://youtu.be/Aff-rX9W_TE?si=EFEr68BfrohDvZMX</p>
 <p>Role Overview</p>
 <p>As the lead person in charge of all engagement and Social Media Marketing, you’ll be the storytelling engine behind SQOR.ai’s daily social media activations, community engagement, and thought leadership posting efforts. You will work as part of the marketing team and closely with branding and ABM, sales, product, and leadership to showcase SQOR.ai’s value proposition to key personas and ICPs (Ideal Customer Profiles).</p>
 <p>MUST be ICP/Persona focused, and data-driven.</p>
 <p>This role is for someone who thrives in fast-paced, high-impact environments and is excited about using all of the traditional SMM tools, as well as the latest AI tools to create and distribute engaging short-form video content, blog posts, social media posts, and maintain interactive discussions with the community.</p>
 <p>Your goal? To drive awareness, engagement, organic growth, and ultimately revenues across all online channels while fostering a community of decision-makers who trust SQOR.ai’s insights.</p>
 <p>Compensation</p>
 <p>This role offers approximately 1% of the company in shares and there is a team of 18 here working full time for equity, doing the same. As we gain traction and raise capital, cash compensation will be introduced, with a timeline targeting Q3 2025 for the first phase of paid compensation.</p>
 <p>Key Responsibilities</p>
 <p>- Create and execute engaging, high-impact social media activations that increase brand awareness, thought leadership, and community engagement across LinkedIn, Twitter, YouTube, and other relevant platforms.</p>
 <p>- Leverage AI-powered content creation tools to produce short-form video content, blog posts, social posts, and interactive discussions; ensuring SQOR.ai maintains a cutting-edge presence online.</p>
 <p>- Engage directly with the community, providing updates, responding to comments, messages, and mentions to build strong relationships and encourage organic discussions around business intelligence, AI, and SaaS.</p>
 <p>- Collaborate with sales and product teams to create social-first content that educates, inspires, and converts key ICPs, including C-suite executives, data professionals, investors, and consultants.</p>
 <p>- Experiment with new social formats, growth hacks, and engagement tactics to increase organic reach and audience interaction.</p>
