INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (195, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/onstation/jobs/51774722-public-relations-and-events-marketing-lead#content', 'Public Relations and Events Marketing Lead', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/onstation?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk1hcmtldGluZyUyMCUyNiUyMENvbW11bmljYXRpb25zIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/b47bbd45-67c5-5225-b56a-1da7a755f13d-1747703970', 'OnStation', 'Marketing & Communications', 1748563200, '<div>
 <p><span>Job Type: Full Time </span></p>
 <p><span>Experience: 3-5 Years Minimum </span></p>
 <p><span>Location: Hybrid, Cleveland, OH </span></p>
 <p><span>Start Date: Flexible </span></p>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>About The Position </strong></p>
 <p>We are seeking a PR &amp; Events Marketing Specialist to spearhead and refine our conference and event strategy while enhancing our public visibility. This position plays a vital role in facilitating event-focused marketing attribution, boosting brand recognition, and supporting our sales team through cohesive campaign execution. From organizing trade shows to elevating our biggest annual event—OnStation Nation—you will bring enthusiasm, coordination, and creativity to every step of the process.</p>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Here is your first mission, should you choose to accept it: On the first LinkedIn question screener, please answer, What is one idea you’d pitch to make the OnStation Nation event for 2025 stand out? </strong></p>
 <p><strong>DM Patrick Russo to answer.</strong></p>
 <p><strong>Who We Are </strong></p>
 <p>The Leading Digital Stationing Platform: With the OnStation app, CAD files for heavy highway road construction projects are viewable on any phone, allowing users to access a live digital station and offset reading wherever they are on the job. Everyone on site can capture what they see without wandering around or wasting time.</p>
 <p>Our app supports a variety of heavy civil road construction organizations, such as asphalt paving companies, engineering/inspection and consulting firms, utilities, subcontractors, concrete pavers, as well as departments of transportation and cities and municipalities. We help them find their location out on the road construction project so they can collaborate and document their work more quickly and more safely.</p>
 <p>Join us in creating a better future where reliable project data (pictures, chats, e-tickets, core tests, and much more) is captured on-site and is visible within the organization’s OnStation’s data portal. We’re helping the people who build our roads do their jobs more easily, and it all begins with the idea, “You are here.”</p>
 <p><strong>The Benefits </strong></p>
 <p><span>At Onstation, we value committed and creative individuals by providing a rewarding work environment that emphasizes collaboration and innovation. We offer stimulating projects, competitive compensation packages—including vacation, PTO, and potential equity—and create a culture where together we strive to build something remarkable. Our foundation lies in developing exceptional solutions for our clients, driving business success and fostering growth in an inspiring workplace. </span></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Full-time salary with performance-based bonus potential</li>
  <li>Health, dental, and vision insurance</li>
  <li>401(k) with company match</li>
  <li>Generous PTO and flexible work schedule</li>
  <li>Opportunity to grow within a high-impact marketing team</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Key Responsibilities </strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>Plan and manage conferences</strong>: Coordinate logistics, booth setup, and speaking engagements.</li>
  <li><strong>Run event campaigns</strong>: Create and optimize pre- and post-event outreach across email, ads, and social.</li>
  <li><strong>Plan OnStation Nation</strong>: Oversee planning, promotion, and execution of our largest annual event.</li>
  <li><strong>Support sales enablement</strong>: Align events with sales goals and provide campaign materials to drive leads.</li>
  <li><strong>Manage PR efforts</strong>: Draft and distribute press releases, coordinate ad placements, and secure earned media coverage.</li>
  <li><strong>Expand brand presence: </strong>Host outward-facing webinars, promote them on LinkedIn, and schedule speaking engagements to showcase our product and demonstrate industry leadership.</li>
  <li><strong>Track results</strong>: Report on event and campaign performance to improve ROI and marketing attribution.</li>
 </ul>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>What will be required in this position </strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li>The most crucial attribute for this role is a solid growth mindset. You must be a self-starter, ready to take charge of your workload and thrive in an independent environment. Be prepared for a fast-paced atmosphere where adaptability is key!</li>
  <li>Genuine enthusiasm for contributing to a rapidly growing company</li>
  <li>Persistence, an unwavering drive, and a high energy level are essential</li>
  <li>Strong organizational and analytical skills with keen attention to detail</li>
  <li>Exceptional communication skills are crucial when engaging with diverse stakeholders across various departments. Cultivating relationships and mastering industry jargon will empower you to create compelling messaging and think outside the box throughout your journey here.</li>
  <li>Experience with HubSpot, MS Office, Notion, and LinkedIn is advantageous.</li>
  <li>A strong ambition to advance within the marketing department or to develop your expertise as an individual contributor</li>
  <li>"Embrace the power of collaboration! Being a team player is essential to our culture, fostering a \'larger than myself’ mindset. Together, we drive collective success that not only achieves our goals but also makes a positive impact. We celebrate teamwork and creativity—‘lone wolf” approaches don\'t align with our vision. Join us on this journey to success!"</li>
  <li><strong>Managing several events and timelines while maintaining thorough oversight is essential.</strong></li>
 </ul>
 <p></p>
 <p><strong>Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) Statement </strong></p>
 <p>At OnStation, we are committed to providing equal employment and advancement opportunities for all individuals, regardless of race, color, religion, sex, national origin, age, disability, or any other characteristic protected by law. We believe that merit-based assessments evaluate individuals based on their abilities, potential, and accomplishments without bias.</p>
 <p>As we strive to revolutionize highway construction management through our innovative application and features, we invite individuals from diverse backgrounds to join us. Our goal is to shape the future of project management in the highway industry and beyond, including expansion into railroads, utilities, and commercial developments. Join us on this journey, showcase your skills, and be part of creating a significant impact in large-scale applications.</p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (196, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lovepop/jobs/51766425-marketing-creative-manager#content', 'Marketing Creative Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lovepop?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk1hcmtldGluZyUyMCUyNiUyMENvbW11bmljYXRpb25zIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/9a080182-994c-5dcd-8c71-283a15851b52-1748396274', 'lovepop', 'Marketing & Communications', 1748563200, '<section>
 <div>
  <b><span>About Lovepop</span></b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Lovepop is on a mission to create one billion magical moments. We combine art x engineering to create the most magical paper art cards &amp; gifts. Featured on Shark Tank in 2015, Lovepop has become one of the top 10 Shark Tank investments in lifetime revenue. Lovepop consistently ranks in the top Google results for cards online, enjoys 18% national brand awareness, and has helped its customers create over 50 million magical moments. Our vision is to be the #1 online card destination for cards and we are building the team of A+ talent that will take us there.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>About the role</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  The Marketing Creative Manager will lead the creative production of high-impact marketing assets across Lovepop’s entire ecosystem. Acting as the crucial link between marketing strategy and creative execution you will work in close collaboration with the Director of Product Marketing, who will define the Awesome Bar for creative. As a team you will bring Lovepop\'s unique brand magic to life through compelling visual storytelling, accelerating customer retention and conversion rates.
 </div>
 <div>
  As Marketing Creative Manager, your mission is to fully own delivery of creative marketing assets for all of Lovepop’s sales channels and scale the Marketing Creative team’s capabilities (rendering, graphic, photography, video, 3D animation). You will direct and mentor a team of talented Vietnam-based designers to deliver marketing materials based on objectives from Marketing, Merchandising, Design, Retail, and Operations. You\'ll drive brand consistency, ensure operational efficiency, and ultimately help us create more magical moments for our customers.
 </div>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Accountabilities</h3>
 <ul>
  <li><b>Creative direction:</b> Inspire and coach your team of designers to create compelling, effective, and brand-building marketing creative.</li>
  <div>
   Provide Creative Direction: Inspire and guide our talented team of designers to take our marketing creative efforts to the next level - providing clear, constructive feedback to ensure all creative output authentically reflects Lovepop\'s unique “art x engineering" brand identity and delivery of magical moments.
  </div>
  <div>
   Lead Creative Production: Own the end-to-end creative production workflow for digital marketing assets (social media ads/posts, email visuals, website banners, digital ad creative, short-form video), from initial brief received through feedback rounds to final, polished delivery, adapting processes for the Marketing Creative team structure.
  </div>
  <div>
   Champion Brand Standards: Act as a dedicated brand guardian for all marketing creative, ensuring visual and tonal consistency with Lovepop\'s guidelines, values, and product aesthetics across every touchpoint. Develop creative marketing assets that build the Lovepop brand.
  </div>
  <div>
   Drive Performance Through Creativity: Partner with channel managers and analytics partners to understand creative performance data. Use these insights to inform creative iterations and future strategies aimed at boosting engagement and conversion (ROAS, CPA, CTR).
  </div>
  <li><b>Process management:</b> Architect an effective and efficient process for our creative pipeline and an organized and effective approach to our asset database.</li>
  <div>
   Drive Process excellence: Work in partnership with the Director of Product Marketing to Implement and manage streamlined asset creation processes across the US and Vietnam organizations. Drive consistent improvement over time. Ensure Lovepop digital assets system is effectively executed and organized.
  </div>
  <div>
   Collaborate Strategically: Work closely with Marketing and Merchandising to deeply understand campaign goals, channel requirements, and target audiences. Translating these needs into compelling visual content, ensuring brand cohesion and project goals are met.
  </div>
  <li><b>A+ team:</b> Lead an A+ Marketing Creative team by recruiting talented people, accurately assessing talent, making quick executive decisions, and providing the team strategic direction, mentorship, and accountability.</li>
  <div>
   Plan and Leverage Resources: plan team capacity and manage resources for all creative marketing projects and hit or exceed all timelines. Plan and scope for training and scaling of rendering, 3D animation, photography, video capabilities to support all marketing initiatives.
  </div>
  <div>
   Build New Capabilities: Recruit, develop and scale product packaging design capabilities within the Marketing Creative team. Contribute to building a culture of excitement and accountability within the Vietnam Design team.
  </div>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Qualifications</h3>
 <ul>
  <li><b>Experience:</b> Minimum 5+ years in creative marketing, creative services, creative production management, or marketing asset management, ideally within a fast-paced e-commerce, DTC, or consumer goods brand. Proven experience managing the end-to-end production of high-volume digital and physical marketing assets (social, email, web, ads, packaging, rendered images, video) is essential. Demonstrated experience leading or providing direction to creative teams, external agencies, and freelancers.</li>
  <li><b>Creative Direction &amp; Judgment:</b> A strong creative eye, a deep understanding of visual storytelling for diverse marketing channels, and the ability to provide clear, constructive feedback.</li>
  <li><b>Creative Tools &amp; Digital Landscape Acumen:</b> Hands-on experience or strong familiarity with creative tools (e.g., Figma, Adobe Creative Suite) and rendering/3D animation software. Solid understanding of key digital marketing channels (especially paid social, email, web), their specific creative requirements, and performance metrics. Awareness of current AI capabilities and the ability to leverage AI for scaling creative development. Understanding of print production processes and packaging design is a plus.</li>
  <li><b>Project Management Prowess:</b> Exceptional organizational skills are a must. You possess the ability to expertly manage multiple complex projects, competing deadlines, and diverse stakeholders simultaneously.</li>
  <li><b>Leadership &amp; Collaboration:</b> Strong interpersonal skills with the ability to lead through influence, foster a collaborative environment (especially with remote/international teams), and build highly effective working relationships with internal teams and external partners.</li>
  <li><b>Strategic Thinking:</b> Ability to embrace creativity and innovation to continuously evolve and improve our creative marketing capabilities and deliverables, while rooted by Lovepop’s brand strategy and longterm goals.</li>
  <li><b>Communication Clarity: </b>Excellent verbal and written communication skills, capable of defining and crafting crystal-clear creative briefs and presenting creative concepts effectively.</li>
  <li><b>Adaptability:</b> You thrive in a dynamic, fast-paced setting, comfortable navigating ambiguity and pivoting strategies based on performance data or shifting priorities.</li>
  <li><b>Portfolio:</b> A strong portfolio showcasing your leadership in the development and production of high-quality, high-performing marketing creative (digital and potentially physical assets), ideally for e-commerce or consumer brands, is required for consideration.</li>
  <li><b>Cultural Fit:</b> A genuine passion for Lovepop\'s mission to create magical moments and a natural alignment with our company values (Engineering, Hunger, Magic, Connection).</li>
  <li><b>Education:</b> Bachelor\'s degree in Marketing, Design, Communications, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <div>
  <b>Lovepop Values</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Engineering</b>: Curiosity to discover how the world works
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Hunger</b>: Desire to take on more than is expected
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Magic</b>: Delivering unexpected experiences
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Connection</b>: Building relationships with each other
 </div>
</section>');
