 <div>
  <span>Outreach is the first and only AI Sales Execution Platform built for intelligent revenue workflows. Built on the world’s largest foundation of customer interactions and go-to-market team data, Outreach’s leading revenue AI technology helps go-to-market professionals and their companies win by intelligently accelerating decision making and elevating sellers to do their best work. Our powerful platform gives revenue teams the tools they need to design, measure, and improve a revenue strategy for every stage of the customer journey, improving efficiency and effectiveness across the entire revenue cycle. Over 6,000 customers, including Zoom, McKesson, Snowflake, SAP, and Okta use Outreach to power workflows, put customers at the center of their business, improve revenue results, and win in the market. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span> </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Outreach is a privately held company based in Seattle, Washington, with offices worldwide. To learn more, please visit </span><a href="https://www.outreach.io/">www.outreach.io</a><span>. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>The role </b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Our mission is to empower every sales professional to operate at their maximum potential unlocking success for themselves and their organization. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span> </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>This is where you come in! </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Do you want to ship industry-defining products for professionals who care about productivity and efficiency? Do you like to design concept models and user flows, as much as executing detailed interaction &amp; UI designs? Then this could be for you! We\'re looking for talented designers with diverse specialties, backgrounds, and perspectives to join our highly skilled international Product Design team. This is an opportunity for a true crafts-person that is passionate about defining seamless workflow experiences that customers love to use every day. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span> </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>You’ll work on our leading AI-powered sales execution platform. Specifically, you’ll design product experiences for our core product line Outreach Engage that accelerates sales prospecting and pipeline generation workflows. You’ll collaborate with teams that own Records Management and Content experiences, and you’ll be able to shape the product experience and its road map significantly. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span> </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Check out a 3-minute demo of our platform: </span><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cHZUYE9lbzc" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cHZUYE9lbzc</a>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Location</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>While we are remote-friendly, we remain an "office-centric" company. This role is categorized as hybrid and it is expected you live in </span><b>a reasonable proximity to the office in Prague</b><span> so you would be able to connect with your team on weekly regular basis, attend in-person meetings and company events.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>This is a full-time, permanent role, not eligible for contractors and for work from other countries.</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>#LI-RG1</span>
 </div>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Your Daily Adventures Will Include</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Craft industry-leading system architectures, seamless user flows, usable interaction models, and highly polished visual UI designs</li>
  <li>Define product experiences that accelerate sales workflows via prospecting, records management, account planning, and multiple generative AI capabilities</li>
  <li>Partner closely with other designers to collaborate and iterate on solutions, and expand our design system patterns.</li>
  <li>Present well-considered design strategies, concepts and prototypes, and communicate the underlying rationale with confidence to your team and company leadership</li>
  <li>Balance customer needs, business goals, and technical considerations to ship well-considered product enhancements that deliver measurable impact</li>
  <li>Partner with our Product Managers to conduct customer interviews, gather qualitative and quantitative insights to support your design work, and run usability studies to evaluate proposed solutions</li>
  <li>Work with a highly adept team of Product, Engineering, and Marketing partners to advance core product capabilities and bring new insights to streamline user flows</li>
  <li>Become an expert in the sales representative persona, their pain points and user needs</li>
  <li>Help us co-create a vibrant inclusive design culture co-created by team members from various geographies (incl. US, CZ, IN) and backgrounds, focused on mutual support and continuous improvement</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Our Vision of You</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>​Have a strong portfolio demonstrating experience in shaping product visions, creating design concepts, customer journeys, beautiful and elegant visual UI designs, and crafting interaction details that solve complex customer problems</li>
  <li>Have experience leading design for a major feature area or vertical independently, and are confident bringing a strong and informed design point of view</li>
  <li>You work with complete autonomy and can lead collaborative working sessions and workshops, across disciplines to meet project objectives</li>
  <li>You’re able to define entirely new product propositions and solve significant interaction complexity and ambiguity without a clear precedent</li>
  <li>Are skilled in presenting and explaining your work, process, decisions, and rationale to cross-functional stakeholders and proactively seek feedback to deliver world-class designs</li>
  <li>Skillfully gauge and adjust your process and deliverable fidelity for proposed solutions to meet the objectives. Including: early vision, conceptual work, information architecture, low fidelity wireframes, user flow prototypes, detailed visual design, and design specifications</li>
  <li>Can work within fast-paced agile teams where close collaboration is part of the daily rhythm. You’re outcome-oriented and not easily overwhelmed or discouraged</li>
  <li>Have experience participating in and driving research activities and utilizing the knowledge of the customer for envisioning novel solutions in undefined problem spaces</li>
  <li>Are a systems thinker and can utilize, propose, and extend shared components, patterns, and interactive behaviors</li>
  <li>Are passionate about the details and always keep pushing your work until it is refined, elegant, and world class</li>
  <li>You exemplify, maintain, and improve our design processes, introducing new methods, frameworks, and tools, to improve team creativity and efficiency</li>
  <li>Have 10+ years of experience in digital product design / UX design / interaction design for software products. <b>Bonus points for having designed workflow-based productivity tools powered by AI</b></li>
  <li>Are uncompromisingly service-minded and anticipate the needs of customers and colleagues with empathy</li>
  <li>You communicate clearly and succinctly, both in written and verbal form, to various audiences across the business, including senior leadership</li>
  <li>You have an inclusive, transparent collaboration style and strong stakeholder management skills. Bonus points for experience collaborating with distributed teams across time zones</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>You should include these in your application:</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>A link to your online portfolio (incl. password)</li>
  <li>Your CV and/or LinkedIn profile</li>
  <li>A few words explaining why Outreach is interesting to you and why you believe it would be a good match</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <div>
  <b>Why You’ll Love It Here</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Amazing working space with a running track on its roof</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Flexible time off, 5 weeks of vacation, and 5 annual sick days</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● 4% employer supplemental pension monthly contribution</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Private medical care for employee and spouse with Program Health Plus </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Life insurance at 2x annual salary</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● 5.000 CZK monthly allowance for meal vouchers, flexipasses and other personal expenses</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● 16 weeks of annual top up maternity leave pay or 8 weeks of fully paid paternity leave</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Opportunity to be part of company success via the RSU program</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Diversity and inclusion programs that promote employee resource groups like OWN+ (Outreach Women\'s Network), Adelante (Latinx community), OBX (Outreach Black Connection), Mosaic (AAPI community), Pride (LGBTQIA+), Gender+, Disability Community, and Veterans/Military </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Employee referral bonuses to encourage the addition of great new people to the team</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>● Fun company and team outings because we play just as hard as we work</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <i><b>Our success is reliant on building teams that include people from different backgrounds and experiences who can elevate assumptions and ideas with fresh perspectives. We\'re dedicated to hiring the whole human, not just a resume. To that end, we look for a diverse pool of applicants-including those from historically marginalized groups. We would like to invite you to apply even if you don\'t think you meet all of the requirements listed below. We don\'t want a few lines in a job description to get between us and the opportunity to meet you.</b></i>
 </div>
</section>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (297, 'https://jobs.techstars.comhttps://hrm.ndb.technology/web/index.php/recruitmentApply/applyVacancy/id/8?utm_source=Techstars+job+board&utm_medium=getro.com&gh_src=Techstars+job+board', 'UX/UI Designer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/gammanics?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkRlc2lnbiJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/8b086348-249c-5de5-8ba9-e1543008a15c-1748136853', 'Gammanics', 'Design', 1747612800, null);
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (298, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lazarus/jobs/50962352-visual-designer#content', 'Visual Designer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lazarus?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkRlc2lnbiJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/5e848455-9ae6-5e25-8d1f-a1196edddc5b-1748828596', 'Lazarus', 'Design', 1747180800, '<p><strong>Job Overview</strong></p>
<p>Our design team is tasked with envisioning AI products that have real-world impact. We have full reign to think expansively and strategically about AI\'s role in helping humans navigate and use data.</p>
<p>We are seeking a skilled and experienced Visual Designer to join our innovative team. As a Visual Designer, you will play a crucial role in creating marketing material, presentations, diagrams, and additional visualizations and media that effectively communicate our foundation models and software products. You will work closely with our design, sales/marketing, and leadership teams to improve the overall quality of our communication.</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Define and develop a cohesive visual identity for Lazarus AI.</li>
 <li>Hands-on creation of assets to enhance Lazarus AI\'s visual presence across all touch-points, such as branding, posters, presentations, web page designs, illustrations, environmental designs, and infographics.</li>
 <li>Work directly with the leadership team and senior stakeholders to present design concepts, gather feedback, and achieve buy-in for visual design strategies.</li>
 <li>Collaborate closely with product design to apply the established visual design framework to the user interface, ensuring a consistent and engaging user experience.</li>
 <li>Design visually appealing and informative data visualizations to present AI-driven insights and solutions that align with the Lazarus brand.</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Bachelor\'s degree in Graphic Design, Visual Communication, related field, or equivalent experience</li>
 <li>4+ years of professional experience in visual design, branding, and marketing, with a strong portfolio demonstrating past work</li>
 <li>Strong understanding of UX best practices, typography, color theory, motion, and layout, coupled with a systems mindset for scalable component libraries.</li>
 <li>Strong conceptual and creative skills with a keen eye for detail</li>
 <li>Proficiency in industry-standard tools such as Adobe Creative Suite, Figma, Google Slides, Keynote, and similar tools</li>
 <li>Exceptional communication and presentation skills, with the ability to articulate design concepts and rationale effectively to diverse audiences, including senior leaders</li>
 <li>Strong project management and organizational skills with the ability to prioritize and manage multiple projects simultaneously</li>
 <li>The ability to execute quick turnaround tasks effectively</li>
 <li>Ability to work collaboratively with cross-functional teams, including product designers, sales team members, and other stakeholders, to translate design visions into functional and visually compelling solutions</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Nice-to-haves</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Experience in B2B SaaS or AI‑driven products.</li>
 <li>Motion design or video editing chops for micro‑interactions and promo content.</li>
 <li>Familiarity with brand strategy, copywriting, or art direction.</li>
 <li>Excellent understanding of UI/UX principles and best practices for designing intuitive and visually appealing user interfaces</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Comprehensive benefits package, including health, dental, and vision insurance, as well as retirement savings plans</li>
 <li>Flexible working from home arrangements</li>
 <li>Opportunities for growth and professional development</li>
 <li>A collaborative and supportive company culture</li>
 <li>Access to cutting-edge technology and resources for research and development</li>
 <li>Compensation (commensurate with experience): $100K - $120K (base salary) + bonus + equity</li>
</ul>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (299, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lazarus/jobs/50962350-senior-product-designer#content', 'Senior Product Designer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lazarus?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkRlc2lnbiJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/5e848455-9ae6-5e25-8d1f-a1196edddc5b-1748828596', 'Lazarus', 'Design', 1747180800, '<p>At Lazarus, we build foundation models to help people solve the world\'s toughest problems. Enterprise and government clients use our APIs to power products and workflows that keep humans focused on what we do best. We\'re a venture-backed team headquartered in the Boston, MA area, and we share a passion for innovation, growth, and a commitment to the responsible use of AI.</p>
<p>You can check out a demo of what we do<a href="https://www.loom.com/share/cf119144b2f5482d9eed650da055389e"> here</a>.</p>
<p><strong><br><br>
  Job Overview</strong></p>
<p>The Senior Product Designer shapes the functional user experience of Lazarus AI products. Equal parts systems thinker and creative storyteller, you thrive on developing designs for cutting-edge AI solutions that make a real impact in the world. You will also have the opportunity to develop high‑impact marketing campaigns, presentations, and visuals, ensuring every touchpoint feels cohesive, intuitive, and unmistakably Lazarus.</p>
<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Design end‑to‑end products—from wireframes through polished UI—ensuring accessibility, responsiveness, and consistency with our design system.</li>
 <li>Create visual assets for campaigns, landing pages, presentations, and events that communicate complex AI concepts with clarity and emotional resonance.</li>
 <li>Maintain and devolve a cross‑functional design system that serves both product and marketing teams, documenting guidelines and facilitating adoption.</li>
 <li>Partner daily with product managers, engineers, and leadership to translate strategic objectives into design solutions, balancing speed and craft.</li>
 <li>Leverage user research, analytics, and A/B testing to iterate on designs and validate assumptions.</li>
 <li>Champion design thinking and visual excellence across the company, presenting work to stakeholders and defending rationale with data and narrative.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>6+ years of professional experience designing digital products and marketing collateral in fast‑paced tech environments.</li>
 <li>Expert proficiency with Figma and Adobe Creative Cloud, with a portfolio demonstrating shipped products and high‑impact visual assets.</li>
 <li>Strong understanding of UX best practices, typography, color theory, motion, and layout, coupled with a systems mindset for scalable component libraries.</li>
 <li>Proven ability to collaborate cross‑functionally, adapt to changing priorities, and deliver high‑quality work under tight deadlines.</li>
 <li>Working knowledge of HTML/CSS and the constraints of modern web technologies.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Nice-to-haves</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Experience in B2B SaaS or AI‑driven products.</li>
 <li>Motion design or video editing chops for micro‑interactions and promo content.</li>
 <li>Familiarity with brand strategy, copywriting, or art direction.</li>
 <li>Comfort running user testing sessions and synthesizing insights into actionable design improvements.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Comprehensive benefits package, including health, dental, and vision insurance, as well as retirement savings plans</li>
 <li>Flexible working from home arrangements</li>
 <li>Opportunities for growth and professional development</li>
 <li>A collaborative and supportive company culture</li>
 <li>Access to cutting-edge technology and resources for research and development</li>
 <li>Compensation (commensurate with experience): $120K - $165K (base salary) + bonus + equity</li>
</ul>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (300, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/glossgenius-2/jobs/50921117-senior-product-designer#content', 'Senior Product Designer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/glossgenius-2?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkRlc2lnbiJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/6939586a-4a89-5cfe-9f3c-e9ba8509e70b-1748310065', 'GlossGenius', 'Design', 1747180800, '<p><strong>About GlossGenius</strong></p>
<p>GlossGenius is building an ecosystem enabling entrepreneurs to succeed. We empower small business owners to focus on being creators, not admins, by offering a range of business management tools including booking and scheduling, marketing, analytics, payment processing and much more.</p>
<p>Over 85,000 small business owners have chosen to rely on GlossGenius every day to run their entire set of business operations. Joining its powerful, intuitive platform with its vibrant, distinguished brand, GlossGenius is the ideal combination of a fintech, SMB software, and consumer company all in one.</p>
<p><strong>About the Role</strong></p>
<p>As a Senior Product Designer, you will lead and own design for one of our product teams focused on attracting and engaging customers to discover all that GlossGenius offers. You’ll own the strategy and execution of growth opportunities together with your Product and Engineering counterpart—from activation and retention to monetization. You’ll spearhead 0-to-1 product innovation, paving the way for new growth initiatives that will shape the next chapter of our business. Our ideal candidate will be able to craft a diverse set of creative solutions to complex product design problems by working with our product team and leadership on the Growth area.</p>
<p>You must be commutable to our NYC headquarters and will operate in a hybrid environment with 2 days per week in the office (Tuesdays &amp; Thursdays).</p>
<p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Own the entire design process, from strategy to execution, of your product area</li>
 <li>Work on the user experience across Growth features within the GlossGenius app</li>
 <li>Own the end-to-end process for solving UX/UI design problems: ideate, conceptualize, test, and refine</li>
 <li>Construct user flows, wireframes, and prototypes that effectively communicate design concepts</li>
 <li>Lead user interviews to better understand customer needs to help inform the product design strategy</li>
 <li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams of product managers, software and QA engineers, customer success managers, and marketers to design intuitive and engaging user experiences for GlossGenius\' customers</li>
 <li>Deliver products that are recognized as the best in the industry by understanding GlossGenius’s strategic and competitive position</li>
 <li>Take initiative in thinking of new ways our users can interact with GlossGenius</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>What We’re Looking For </strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>4+ years of experience in a Product Design/UX/UI or related role; prior experience in Growth is a plus</li>
 <li>Demonstrated experience with sketching, wireframes, visual design, and prototyping for product experiences</li>
 <li>Experience with advanced prototyping tools (e.g. Principle, Framer, Sketch, Figma, InVision)</li>
 <li>Proven experience leveraging current AI tools within the design process</li>
 <li>Passion for empowering small business owners to be successful; possess a high level of empathy our customers and a strong desire to deeply understand their needs</li>
 <li>Experience navigating ambiguous high-growth, fast-paced product-driven environments</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Benefits &amp; Perks</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Flexible PTO</li>
 <li>Competitive health &amp; dental insurance options, with premiums partially covered by GG</li>
 <li>Fertility and adoption benefits via Carrot and Kindbody</li>
 <li>Generous, fully-paid parental leave policy</li>
 <li>401k benefit - employees are eligible to contribute starting day 1 of employment</li>
 <li>Professional Development - employees receive a yearly stipend for approved learning and educational-related expenses</li>
 <li>Pre-tax commuter benefits</li>
 <li>Dependent Care FSA</li>
 <li>Team Bonding: As a distributed team, being able to build meaningful bonds both virtually and in person is incredibly important to us! We are constantly evaluating how we accomplish this and currently, teams are given opportunities to gather in person throughout the year</li>
</ul>
<p>The starting base salary for this role in New York and California is between <em>$170,000-$210,000 +</em> target equity + benefits. The base salary offered is dependent upon many factors including skills, experience, location, and education. The base pay range is subject to change and may be modified in the future.</p>
<p><em>At GlossGenius, we celebrate our differences and are committed to creating a workplace where all employees feel supported and empowered to do their best work. We believe this benefits not only our employees but our product, customers, and community as well. GlossGenius is proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action Employer.</em></p>
<div>
 <p><a href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1FF_5dYGdwHfNCMqV4X9NSnCLdnk9z7Ms/view?usp=sharing"><em>Personal Information: Notice at Collection for Employees and Applicants</em></a></p>
 <p><em>Agency Submissions<br></em><em>If a resume or applicant is submitted to GlossGenius by a third party without a signed search agreement in place, it will become the property of GlossGenius and no fee will be paid, irrespective of whether the candidate is hired. </em></p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (301, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lovepop/jobs/50892561-ui-ux-designer#content', 'UI/UX Designer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/lovepop?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIkRlc2lnbiJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/9a080182-994c-5dcd-8c71-283a15851b52-1748396274', 'lovepop', 'Design', 1747180800, '<section>
 <div>
  <b><span>About Lovepop</span></b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Lovepop is on a mission to create one billion magical moments. We combine art x engineering to create the most magical paper art cards &amp; gifts. Featured on Shark Tank in 2015, Lovepop has become one of the top 10 Shark Tank investments in lifetime revenue. Lovepop consistently ranks in the top Google results for cards online, enjoys 18% national brand awareness, and has helped its customers create over 50 million magical moments. Our vision is to be the #1 online card destination for cards and we are building the team of A+ talent that will take us there.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>About the roles</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>As UI/UX designer you will own the creating designs that elevate the customer experience for </span><a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a><span>. Your mission is to lead and influence Lovepop to ensure that we are consistently and reliably delivering the right solutions on </span><a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a><span> for our customers to help them find the right product for their special person. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>This role is a great fit for someone who thrives in a dynamic environment, empathizes with customers, and has experience working with engineering teams in a small to medium size startup company. You will need to constantly look for optimization areas, work with marketing, customer service, operations and tech to create a compelling experience for our customers. Ability to influence, analytical ability, strong tracking/monitoring capabilities, exceptional communication skills and leadership are essential to success in this role.</span>
 </div>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Accountabilities</h3>
 <ul>
  <li><b>Owns creating great UX design for the customer on <a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a>: </b>You will deliver UX designs for a variety of small and large projects that will improve the customer experience on <a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a> and drive innovative ideas. Leverage quantitative and qualitative data to discover new opportunities to improve the site that creates a more compelling experience for our customers. Demonstrate an understanding of user behavior and can speak to cause-and-effect. You are seen as the expert in your space and often bring clarity to difficult <a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a> UX issues.</li>
  <li><b>Own the customer experience on <a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a>: </b> You actively research and discover opportunities to improve the customer experience. Performs customer research to discover customer needs and pain points on the existing <a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a> experience. Actively promotes ideas that improve the customer experience. Anticipates bottlenecks and makes tradeoffs to balance the business needs versus technical constraints. Leverages A/B testing to gain early signals from customers on new UX features.</li>
  <li><b>Build strong relationships between technology and the stakeholder that we serve: </b>Interact closely with the Lovepop business teams to discover new opportunities to improve the UX on <a href="http://Lovepop.com" rel="noopener noreferrer">Lovepop.com</a>. Leads efforts internally to educate internal teams on UX pain points. Works with business owners to validate assumptions and asks questions to fill in knowledge gaps to ensure that the correct features are being built for our customers.</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Qualifications</h3>
 <ul>
  <li><b>2+ Years Online DTC Experience: </b>Lovepop is an online card selling company and the person filling this role needs to have extensive experiences in innovating and delivering projects that have improved the purchasing process, browse experience and other parts of the online experience. The successful candidate for this position must have direct ownership experience in Online DTC processes and not just worked in an Ecommerce company.</li>
  <li><b>5+ Years of UX Experience: </b>This role will play a very critical part in driving the success of executing initiatives and projects in Lovepop. This person will be expected to immediately be impacting our roadmaps by working with Product Managers and other senior leaders to understand existing priorities but also shape new priorities including ones we might not have thought about.</li>
  <li><b>Experience in a Fast Pace and Sometime Ambiguous Environment: </b>Lovepop is at the forefront of learning to sell cards online. We move fast to try new ideas and adapt quickly to the needs of our customers. The person in this role needs to drive projects to be delivered quickly, accurately measure the impact and adapt to the results.</li>
  <li><b>Think Outside the Box:</b> Selling greeting cards online requires new thinking about how to serve our customers the best. This role requires a person to think about how we develop new experiences for the customer to create the right card for their special person.</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <div>
  <b>Lovepop Values</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Engineering</b><span>: Curiosity to discover how the world works</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Hunger</b><span>: Desire to take on more than is expected</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Magic</b><span>: Delivering unexpected experiences</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Connection</b><span>: Building relationships with each other</span>
