   <h4><strong>Real Estate &amp; Facilities Support</strong></h4>
   <ul>
    <li>Coordinate lease-related documents with landlords, including estoppels, SNDAs, and draft leases.</li>
    <li>Obtain and manage Certificates of Insurance (COIs); liaise with insurance brokers and landlords regarding coverage and lease terms.</li>
    <li>Send draft leases to insurance brokers for review of insurance provisions.</li>
   </ul>
   <h4><strong>Regulatory, Litigation, &amp; Compliance</strong></h4>
   <ul>
    <li>Conduct sanctions checks and assist with annual report filings.</li>
    <li>Assist in gathering documents and preparing responses to subpoenas.</li>
   </ul>
   <h4><strong>Document &amp; Project Management</strong></h4>
   <ul>
    <li>Organize and save executed contracts in designated systems and folders (e.g., Real Estate Drive).</li>
    <li>Coordinate document notarization, signing, and mailing.</li>
    <li>Manage scheduling and communications with stakeholders regarding contract logistics.</li>
    <li>Assist in project management tasks and legal operations initiatives.</li>
   </ul>
   <h4><strong>Legal Research &amp; Communication</strong></h4>
   <ul>
    <li>Perform light legal research using Westlaw or similar tools.</li>
    <li>Draft internal and external email communications for legal or operational matters.</li>
    <li>Coordinate with cross-functional teams to ensure smooth execution of legal processes.</li>
   </ul>
   <h3><strong>What you bring</strong></h3>
   <ul>
    <li>5+ years of experience as a paralegal, contract manager, or similar role, preferably in an in-house legal department.</li>
    <li>Strong understanding of contracts, leases, and legal document management.</li>
    <li>Exceptional organizational skills and attention to detail.</li>
    <li>Excellent communication skills—written and verbal—with internal and external stakeholders.</li>
    <li>Familiarity with tools such as Google Workspace, contract management software, and legal research platforms (e.g., Westlaw).</li>
    <li>Ability to manage multiple projects and deadlines simultaneously.</li>
    <li>Experience supporting legal functions.</li>
    <li>Notary public certification or experience coordinating notarizations is a plus.</li>
