INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (405, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline/jobs/52737585-senior-gnc-engineer#content', 'Senior GNC Engineer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk90aGVyJTIwRW5naW5lZXJpbmciXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/716c870c-b07d-50ff-ab75-427af872bf20-1740432205', 'Zipline', 'Other Engineering', 1750118400, '<h3><strong>About Zipline</strong></h3>
<p>Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building, manufacturing and operating the first instant delivery and logistics system that serves all humans equally, wherever they are. From powering Rwanda’s national blood delivery network and Ghana’s COVID-19 vaccine distribution, to providing on-demand home delivery for Walmart, to enabling healthcare providers to bring care directly to U.S. homes, we are transforming the way things move for businesses, governments and consumers.</p>
<p>The technology is complex but the idea is simple: a teleportation service that delivers what you need, when you need it. Through our technology that includes robotics and autonomy, we are decarbonizing delivery, decreasing road congestion, and reducing fossil fuel consumption and air pollution, while providing equitable access to billions of people and building a more resilient global supply chain.</p>
<p>Join Zipline and help us to make good on our promise to build an equitable and more resilient global supply chain for billions of people.</p>
<h3><strong>About You and The Role </strong></h3>
<p>Zipline’s GNC team is at the heart of our product’s success. Our team is responsible for modeling, developing, and testing the tools and critical flight software systems that enable our aircraft to complete missions autonomously and that enable Zipline to rapidly iterate and improve our products. We thrive on developing novel solutions to ensure our delivery platforms can function in a wide range of increasingly challenging conditions, ensuring that we serve everyone in the world equally. From pushing the limits of the hardware to informing changes to improve resilience and manufacturing; GNC analysis is central to our continued success.</p>
<p>In this role you’ll use a range of analysis techniques to understand our system performance and how it is affected by design choices, limitations and requirements, as well as proactively collaborating across teams to drive improvements to our products. Working with the wider team, you’ll use data from flight testing and our global fleet of customer aircraft to improve simulations and develop tools to continually find new insights that will improve our products. By staying close to our customers, you’ll learn what really works and where we should be spending our time to drive our next phase of growth. Success in this role leads directly to improved operational capability of our logistics network.</p>
<h3><strong>What You\'ll Do </strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>Develop dynamic models of complex systems and components that are core to our high fidelity 6DOF simulation.</li>
 <li>Analyze and improve the performance of existing and future vehicle designs through a combination of simulation and flight tests.</li>
 <li>Play a key role in deriving and verifying requirements for both hardware components and software interfaces, while balancing the technical need and broader product prerequisites as well as safety and regulatory standards.</li>
 <li>Identify and develop processes and tools to improve efficiency and protect against regressions.</li>
 <li>Design and implement onboard integrity tests to monitor how well the aircraft is flying and aid in understanding off-nominal performance and flight failures, both in research and validation flights, as well as in the production fleet.</li>
 <li>Work in a high performing team, sharing your experience and improving efficiency while developing the next generation of logistics.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>What You\'ll Bring </strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>Professional experience in one or more of the following areas: flight dynamics and control, dynamic modeling of complex physical systems, model identification, statistical analysis. Ideally you will have used your skills in these areas to successfully ship one or more complex products.</li>
 <li>Demonstrate enthusiasm and proficiency in both simulation practices and hands-on work with hardware, spanning from bench-level experimentation to comprehensive flight tests.</li>
 <li>Software skills in both technical computing (MATLAB, SciPi, Julia, etc) and embedded software (Rust, C, C++), with experience working in a large, complex, multi-developer environment.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>What Else You Need to Know </strong></h3>
<p>The starting cash range for this role is $<span>170,000 - $210,000</span>. Please note that this is a target, starting cash range for a candidate who meets the minimum qualifications for this role. The final cash pay for this role will depend on a variety of factors, including a specific candidate\'s experience, qualifications, skills, working location, and projected impact. The total compensation package for this role may also include: equity compensation; discretionary annual or performance bonuses; sales incentives; benefits such as medical, dental and vision insurance; paid time off; and more.</p>
<p>Zipline is an equal opportunity employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, ancestry, national origin, religion or religious creed, mental or physical disability, medical condition, genetic information, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, and related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital status, military or veteran status, citizenship, or other characteristics protected by state, federal or local law or our other policies.</p>
<p>We value diversity at Zipline and welcome applications from those who are traditionally underrepresented in tech. If you like the sound of this position but are not sure if you are the perfect fit, please apply!</p>');
INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (406, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/bevi/jobs/52689871-electrical-engineer#content', 'Electrical Engineer', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/bevi?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk90aGVyJTIwRW5naW5lZXJpbmciXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/c3b9554a-a9d2-5ec6-a38f-25e970d9d6f2-1748914080', 'Bevi', 'Other Engineering', 1750032000, '<p>Bevi is on a mission to disrupt the beverage supply chain and replace single-use water bottles with smart water machines. Thousands of companies use Bevi to sustainably provide their employees with pure, sparkling, and flavored water at work. As the market leader in IoT-enabled beverage machines, we’ve raised over $160M in venture capital and we have grown tremendously each year since launch. In addition to maintaining hypergrowth with our current product line, Bevi is heavily investing in new product development.</p>
<p>We are searching for an Electrical Engineer who is excited to work on our hardware product with a cloud-based back-end and help bring new ideas from prototype to production. We’re looking for someone who has worked with PCBA designs that include networking, sensing and interfacing with other hardware components, who is ready to jump in and help continually improve our existing products as well as support the development of the next generation of products.</p>
<p><strong>PLEASE NOTE: This position is based in our Boston, MA office. Candidates must be available to work onsite at least three days per week. </strong></p>
<h3>Your Day to Day</h3>
<ul>
 <li>Investigate and propose design architectures for complex electrical systems</li>
 <li>Work cross-functionally to develop reliable, high-quality products</li>
 <li>Be involved in all steps of the electrical engineering process, from establishing design specifications to product launch, including validation and sustaining efforts</li>
 <li>Develop circuits and PCB designs including power, high-speed, RF and networking circuits</li>
 <li>Ensure design compliance with EMI/EMC requirements</li>
 <li>Be responsible for releasing of ECAD/EDA exports and generation of ECOs in the PLM system</li>
 <li>Perform electrical failure investigations by gathering data and using root cause analysis techniques</li>
 <li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to develop requirements, specifications, and validation plans</li>
 <li>Support the product development lifecycle by providing electrical engineering expertise</li>
 <li>Develop best practices for reliability and quality of electrical subsystems</li>
 <li>Provide mentorship and support to junior engineers and co-ops</li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li>BS or MS in Electrical Engineering or in a similar field with 6+ years of industry experience in product development (consumer/industrial), sustaining, or technology exploration in Robotics, Networking, Sensing, IoT or related fields</li>
 <li>Strong knowledge of circuit design,multi-layer PCBs, high speed signaling, RF, and embedded systems</li>
 <li>Expertise in using schematic capture and PCB layout tools (e.g. Altium Designer)</li>
 <li>Experience in designing and implementing solutions that require integration with electrical and mechanical components</li>
 <li>Proficiency in the use of signal acquisition/analysis tools such as oscilloscopes, DMMs, logic analyzers, data loggers, and spectrum analyzers</li>
 <li>Experience in PCB bring-up, debugging and validation, including ability to rework SMT/TH circuit components and producing bring-up test code</li>
 <li>Familiarity with DFM and DFT as it relates to PCBA design and component/device selection</li>
 <li>Knowledge of industry standards and compliance (e.g. FCC, CE, UL)</li>
 <li>Strong understanding of firmware development fundamentals (C/C++)</li>
 <li>Ability to take initiative and thrive in a fast-paced environment</li>
 <li>A team-oriented approach to problem solving and knowledge generation</li>
 <li>Experience working in scaling start-ups is a plus</li>
 <li>Ability to be in the office 3+ days per week</li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li>Comprehensive medical, dental and vision insurance plans with BlueCross BlueShield, 95% paid by employer</li>
 <li>401(k) with company match, and environmentally responsible investment options</li>
 <li>Flexible PTO plus 12 company holidays, and additional paid days for sick leave, etc (including sustainability or social justice volunteer events)</li>
 <li>Generous fully paid parental leave for both birth parents and non-birth parents</li>
 <li>Fully employer paid disability and life insurances</li>
 <li>Wellness and fitness reimbursements</li>
 <li>Monthly stipends for cell phone use and commuting costs</li>
 <li>Onsite snacks, weekly catered lunch, and (of course) unlimited Bevi ... plus composting and terracycling, too</li>
 <li>Happy hours, team-building events, bagel breakfasts, Hero awards - and more.</li>
</ul>
<p>We\'re excited about supporting career growth and would love to be part of your professional journey. We know that talent comes in many forms, and we value individual accomplishments, specialized knowledge, and genuine passion over just checking boxes on a requirements list.If any of our positions interest you, please apply! Our recruiting team will contact you about next steps if we\'d like to move forward together.</p>');
