INSERT INTO job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (409, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/blink/jobs/52689393-engineering-manager#content', 'Engineering Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/blink?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIk90aGVyJTIwRW5naW5lZXJpbmciXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/022f02dc-dcc5-5059-a769-a462498aefde-1748914565', 'Blink', 'Other Engineering', 1750032000, '<p><strong>📍 Location: London (Old Street office, 3 days/week). </strong></p>
<p><strong>🌍 Join a high-growth, mission-driven tech company that’s transforming the future of work.</strong></p>
<p><strong>📣 Reports to: CTO. </strong></p>
<h3><strong>👋 About Blink</strong></h3>
<p>Blink is an employee app for frontline workers, with industry-leading engagement and a DAU of 99%. We’re dedicated to scaling our platform through precision, automation, and innovation. As part of a world-class engineering team, you’ll play a key role in shaping the future of how we support frontline workers.</p>
<h3>💻 <strong>The Role</strong></h3>
<p>We’re looking for a pragmatic, delivery-focused Engineering Manager to lead two of our Product &amp; Engineering (P&amp;E) teams. You\'ll drive effective execution, uphold engineering standards, and support first-time managers in adjacent teams. Though this is not a hands-on coding role, your technical experience will help unblock teams when needed.</p>
<h3>Key Responsibilities:</h3>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Lead two cross-functional P&amp;E teams:</strong> with a focus on high-quality, timely delivery, you’ll ensure work is well-defined, prioritised, and continuously flowing.</li>
 <li><strong>Champion Agile Execution:</strong> Instil and evolve Agile and Kanban-based workflows. You\'ll help teams break work into manageable increments, visualise progress, and improve flow efficiency over time.</li>
 <li><strong>Enable High-Quality Engineering:</strong> Promote robust engineering practices — including code reviews, CI/CD, automated testing, and clear documentation — to support sustainable delivery.</li>
 <li><strong>Mentor New Leaders:</strong> Coach and support team leads in adjacent groups who are taking their first steps into engineering management, helping them build confidence and delivery discipline.</li>
 <li><strong>Drive Cross-Functional Collaboration:</strong> Work closely with Product, Design, and Platform stakeholders to ensure alignment on priorities and outcomes.</li>
 <li><strong>Support When Needed:</strong> While not a coding role, your background allows you to dive into technical discussions, triage urgent issues, and assist in unblocking teams when necessary.</li>
</ul>
<h3>🚀 About you:</h3>
<p>We’re looking for a talented, ambitious individual who thrives in a fast-paced, growing environment. You should be a resourceful, inquisitive, and quick learner, with a passion for solving customer problems and making a real impact. In addition, you will have:</p>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Proven Leadership:</strong> Experience managing multiple engineering teams, ideally in a fast-paced, product-led environment.</li>
 <li><strong>Delivery-Oriented Mindset:</strong> A strong track record of delivering complex features or initiatives on time — and helping others do the same.</li>
 <li><strong>Agile &amp; Kanban Fluency:</strong> Deep familiarity with Kanban and Agile principles, including work-in-progress limits, cycle time measurement, and continuous improvement.</li>
 <li><strong>Engineering Acumen:</strong> Solid foundation in modern software development practices, with the ability to engage credibly in technical discussions.</li>
 <li><strong>Collaborative Style:</strong> A team-first, low-ego approach to leadership. Skilled in balancing team health with accountability and focus.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>💚 </strong>Why Blink?</h3>
<ul>
 <li>You will have the opportunity to be part of something impactful, large-scale, and meaningful.</li>
 <li>Most importantly, you’ll work for a company with a strong purpose, with an ambitious and supportive team embarking on a journey most start-ups can only dream of!</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Benefits include:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Competitive salary and generous equity allocations with significant upside potential</li>
 <li>25 days annual leave per year (+ public holidays!)</li>
 <li>The equipment needed to do a great job</li>
 <li>Private healthcare</li>
 <li>Cycle to Work scheme</li>
 <li>Social events (company getaways, lunches, breakfasts, nights out)</li>
