INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (456, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/flashfood/jobs/51620202-director-people-culture-contract#content', 'Director, People & Culture (Contract)', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/flashfood?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlBlb3BsZSUyMCUyNiUyMEhSIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/b4ead5ea-07d5-5953-b8df-80e1db544e0a-1749173371', 'Flashfood', 'People & HR', 1748390400, '<p><span>*12 month contract</span></p>
<p><span>Who You Are</span></p>
<p><span>We are looking for a passionate and experienced People &amp; Culture professional who wants to help combat food waste, and thrives on building meaningful and sustainable relationships with people. This Director of People &amp; Culture will support our team to deliver and implement P&amp;C programs and services while keeping our people at the heart of everything we do. We can only create a better company together by living our shared values, and preserving our unique culture as we continue to grow. </span></p>
<p><span>People &amp; Culture</span></p>
<ul>
 <li><span>Mentor &amp; coach our People &amp; Culture team, and continue to develop a high performing &amp; engaged team</span></li>
 <li><span>Lead and execute our compensation strategy, including annual comp surveys, managing our annual compensation increase process and ongoing promotional processes</span></li>
 <li><span>Manage our group benefits plan in Canada and US to ensure we are keeping up with market trends and managing annual renewals with our brokers</span></li>
 <li><span>Become an expert on our stock option plan, including educating our team, supporting finance with granting and exercising teammates options</span></li>
 <li><span>Act as a collaborative partner with our Leadership team, ensuring alignment between each department and P&amp;C by providing insightful, solutions-oriented, and empathetic problem solving</span></li>
 <li><span>Manage the People &amp; Culture budget, including employee salaries and benefits</span></li>
 <li><span>Leverage data and best practices to optimize P&amp;C, and guide decisions with respect to hiring, talent development programs, and retention</span></li>
 <li><span>Review and update policies and procedures to ensure compliance across both US and Canada </span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span>Build on remote work best practices, ensuring our teams are set up for success </span></li>
 <li><span>Identify organizational training needs and develop and implement training courses that satisfy these needs</span></li>
 <li><span>Support our P&amp;C Generalist with our recruitment process. This may include participation in the full cycle of the recruitment and onboarding process</span></li>
 <li><span>Leading and reporting on our annual KPI’s and team objectives </span></li>
 <li><span>Lead the organization’s performance management program </span></li>
 <li><span>Approving and overseeing the P&amp;C payroll process in partnership with Finance</span></li>
 <li><span>Maintain and optimize HRIS (data integrity, tracking, reporting)</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span>Risk Management </span></p>
<ul>
 <li><span>Support our GRC Analyst in developing and managing the company’s risk management framework to identify and mitigate risks.</span></li>
 <li><span>Ensure compliance with regulatory and industry standards through policy creation and enforcement.</span></li>
 <li><span>Conduct risk assessments and audits across operational, financial, and IT areas.</span></li>
 <li><span>Monitor and address changes in legal and regulatory requirements.</span></li>
 <li><span>Promote a culture of compliance and risk awareness through training and communication.</span></li>
 <li><span>Present risk reports and recommendations</span><span> to leadership </span></li>
</ul>
<p><span>What you bring to the team:</span></p>
<ul>
 <li><span>10+ years of HR/People Operations, 3-5 of which you’ve led a function/team.</span></li>
 <li><span>Experience in scaling, high-growth companies, experience working in tech a plus! </span></li>
 <li><span>Excellent relationship-building skills, passion for customer service</span></li>
 <li><span>Post-secondary education in HR or equivalent work experience</span></li>
 <li><span>Meticulous attention to detail and accuracy</span></li>
 <li><span>Excellent skills in G Suite</span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
 <li><span>Experience working with an HRIS and Performance Management Software</span></li>
 <li><span>Solid project management skills and effective time management/prioritization skills</span></li>
 <li><span>Demonstrated ability to use sound judgment and decision-making skills when faced with conflict situations or sensitive employee relations matters</span></li>
