INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (472, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/preply/jobs/50024201-strategy-planning-lead-people#content', 'Strategy & Planning Lead - People', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/preply?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlBlb3BsZSUyMCUyNiUyMEhSIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/bd8a3585-967c-5c75-b55d-2fe6d8e2962c-1749087038', 'Preply', 'People & HR', 1745971200, '<h3><strong>We power people’s progress. </strong></h3>
<p>At Preply, we’re all about creating life-changing learning experiences. We help people discover the magic of the perfect tutor, craft a personalized learning journey, and stay motivated to keep growing. Our approach is human-led, tech-enabled - and it’s creating real impact. So far, 90,000 tutors have delivered over 20 million lessons to learners in more than 175 countries. Every Preply lesson sparks change, fuels ambition, and drives progress that matters.</p>
<h3><strong>Meet the team!</strong></h3>
<p>The People team is responsible for the entire lifecycle of the employee journey at Preply, including onboarding and offboarding compliance, total rewards and benefits, HR systems and analytics as well as key People projects such as employee engagement, career development and frameworks and others.</p>
<p>You will take on a high-impact, cross-functional role where you will partner closely with our Leadership team, driving strategic projects and making sure we’re set up for scale, efficiency, and impact.</p>
<h3><strong>What you’ll be doing:</strong></h3>
<p><strong>Strategic Planning &amp; Execution:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>
  <div>
   Lead annual planning cycles for the People team, aligning roadmaps, OKRs, and budgets with company priorities.
  </div></li>
 <li>
  <div>
   Track progress on key initiatives and drive accountability across leaders, ensuring follow-through and results.
  </div></li>
 <li>
  <div>
   Partner with the People Leadership on org-wide strategy updates and board-level content.
  </div></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Leadership Communication:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>
  <div>
   Own meetings - creating agendas, summarizing insights, and keeping the People Leadership team focused on what matters most.
  </div></li>
 <li>
  <div>
   Act as a thought partner to the VP People, preparing internal and external communications that elevate our People strategy and culture.
  </div></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Data &amp; Insights:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>
  <div>
   Continuously monitor, analyze and improve tracking of key People metrics such as attrition, engagement, performance, hiring, and organizational health.
  </div></li>
 <li>
  <div>
   Translate data into strategic insights and trends that drive decision-making across the People team.
  </div></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Special Projects:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p>Lead priority cross-functional initiatives such as leadership enablement, AI integration, and IPO readiness from the People lens.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>What you need to succeed:</strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>5+ years of experience in a Strategy or Business Operations role, preferably with a track record in people-related projects.</li>
 <li>Experience in a top-tier consultancy and/or in-house experience in a hyper-growth environment.</li>
 <li>Strong analytical thinking, paired with excellent communication and storytelling skills.</li>
 <li>Comfortable navigating data and connecting the dots to drive smart decisions.</li>
 <li>Business or economics academic background is a plus.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Why you’ll love it at Preply:</strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>An open, collaborative, dynamic and diverse culture;</li>
 <li>A generous monthly allowance for lessons on <a href="http://preply.com">Preply.com</a>, Learning &amp; Development budget and time off for your self-development;</li>
 <li>A competitive financial package with equity, leave allowance and health insurance;</li>
 <li>Not in Barcelona? We offer an attractive relocation package to join us in our Preply Barcelona Hub</li>
 <li>Access to free mental health support platforms;</li>
 <li>Access to Gympass-partnered wellness and gym centers throughout Spain to promote and support well-being and physical health;</li>
 <li>The opportunity to unlock the potential of learners and tutors through language learning and teaching in 175 countries (and counting!).</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Our Principles</strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li><strong>Care to change the world</strong> - We are passionate about our work and care deeply about its impact to be life changing.</li>
 <li><strong>We do it for learners</strong> - For both Preply and tutors, learners are why we do what we do. Every day we focus on empowering tutors to deliver an exceptional learning experience.</li>
 <li><strong>Keep perfecting </strong>- To create an outstanding customer experience, we focus on simplicity, smoothness, and enjoyment, continually perfecting it as every detail matters.</li>
 <li><strong>Now is the time</strong> - In a fast-paced world, it matters how quickly we act. Now is the time to make great things happen.</li>
 <li><strong>Disciplined execution</strong> - What makes us disciplined is the excellence in our execution. We set clear goals, focus on what matters, and utilize our resources efficiently.</li>
 <li><strong>Dive deep</strong> - We leverage business acumen and curiosity to investigate disparities between numbers and stories, unlocking meaningful insights to guide our decisions.</li>
 <li><strong>Growth mindset</strong> - We proactively seek growth opportunities and believe today\'s best performance becomes tomorrow\'s starting point. We humbly embrace feedback and learn from setbacks.</li>
 <li><strong>Raise the bar</strong> - We raise our performance standards continuously, alongside each new hire and promotion. We build diverse and high-performing teams that can make a real difference.</li>
 <li><strong>Challenge, disagree and commit</strong> - We value open and candid communication, even when we don’t fully agree. We speak our minds, challenge when necessary, and fully commit to decisions once made.</li>
 <li><strong>One Preply </strong>- We prioritize collaboration, inclusion, and the success of our team over personal ambitions. Together, we support and celebrate each other\'s progress.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion</strong></h3>
<p>Preply is committed to creating a diverse and inclusive environment where people from all backgrounds can thrive. Different opinions and viewpoints are key ingredients in our success as a multicultural Ed-Tech company.</p>
<p>Preply will consider all applications for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, disability, age or veteran status. Together, we are The World Class.</p>
<p>#LI-VS1</p>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (473, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline/jobs/50010564-people-data-specialist#content', 'People Data Specialist', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlBlb3BsZSUyMCUyNiUyMEhSIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/716c870c-b07d-50ff-ab75-427af872bf20-1740432205', 'Zipline', 'People & HR', 1745971200, '<h3><strong>About Zipline</strong></h3>
<div>
 Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building, manufacturing and operating the first instant delivery and logistics system that serves all humans equally, wherever they are. From powering Rwanda’s national blood delivery network and Ghana’s COVID-19 vaccine distribution, to providing on-demand home delivery for Walmart, to enabling healthcare providers to bring care directly to U.S. homes, we are transforming the way things move for businesses, governments and consumers. The technology is complex but the idea is simple: a teleportation service that delivers what you need, when you need it. Using robotics and autonomy, we are decarbonizing delivery, decreasing road congestion, and reducing fossil fuel consumption and air pollution, while providing equitable access to billions of people and building a more resilient global supply chain.
</div>
<div>
</div>
<div>
 Join Zipline and help us to make good on our promise to build an equitable and more resilient global supply chain for billions of people.
</div>
<div>
 <h3><strong>About You and The Role </strong></h3>
 <p>Join us in shaping a data-driven People Strategy! At Zipline, we believe our people are our greatest asset—and that data is the key to unlocking their full potential. We’re looking for a People Data Analyst who thrives on transforming complexity into clarity. If you\'re someone who lives in spreadsheets, loves uncovering patterns, and is excited to influence how we hire, develop, and reward our talent—this role is for you.</p>
 <p>This is a high-impact opportunity to partner across People, Total Rewards, and business leadership teams to drive better decisions through data. You’ll play a central role in building scalable analytics, uncovering insights that shape our employee experience, and helping us continuously raise the bar.</p>
 <h3>What You\'ll Do</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Leverage your expertise in quantitative analysis and the presentation of data to see beyond the numbers and help inform, influence, support, and execute our compensation strategy</li>
  <li>Build and maintain dashboards, reports, and analyses using Excel, Google Sheets, and other BI tools to support HR, Talent, and Total Rewards initiatives.</li>
  <li>Support our bi-annual global compensation planning process end-to-end including design &amp; management of the tooling, equity plan design, lead engagement and overall communication strategy across the company</li>
  <li>Select appropriate benchmark surveys, analyze and interpret relevant market data, and develop recommendations for updates to job categories and salary structures as appropriate</li>
  <li>Support the recruiting team with all new hire compensation offers, including market trend analysis and offer negotiations</li>
  <li>Ensure data accuracy and integrity through rigorous attention to detail and proactive auditing.</li>
  <li>Continuously improve processes, models, and templates to enable scale and operational excellence.</li>
 </ul>
 <h3>What You\'ll Bring</h3>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>2+ years</strong> of experience in data analysis, people analytics, HR operations, or a related data-driven role.</li>
  <li><strong>Advanced Excel and Google Sheets</strong> skills—you’re comfortable with complex formulas, pivot tables, and data validation.</li>
  <li>A <strong>keen eye for detail</strong> and a high bar for data quality and accuracy.</li>
  <li><strong>Strong communication skills</strong>—able to explain technical findings to non-technical audiences clearly and confidently.</li>
  <li><strong>Project management</strong> chops—you know how to drive work forward, align stakeholders, and deliver on time.</li>
  <li>Professionalism and discretion in handling sensitive data</li>
  <li>Strong work ethic and team-first attitude: humility and humor make for a high-impact contributor</li>
  <li>Bonus: Experience supporting <strong>compensation, total rewards, or workforce planning</strong> functions.</li>
 </ul>
 <h3>What Else You Need to Know</h3>
 <div>
  <div>
   Zipline is an equal opportunity employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, ancestry, national origin, religion or religious creed, mental or physical disability, medical condition, genetic information, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, and related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital status, military or veteran status, citizenship, or other characteristics protected by state, federal or local law or our other policies.
  </div>
  <div>
  </div>
  <div>
   We value diversity at Zipline and welcome applications from those who are traditionally underrepresented in tech. If you like the sound of this position but are not sure if you are the perfect fit, please apply!
  </div>
 </div>
</div>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (474, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/novo-2/jobs/49645669-lead-recruiter#content', 'Lead Recruiter', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/novo-2?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlBlb3BsZSUyMCUyNiUyMEhSIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/1d135d22-24a6-58aa-a8ef-5a65f54af7e8-1748049974', 'Novo', 'People & HR', 1745366400, '<div>
 <p><span>We started Novo to challenge the status quo— we’re on a mission to build the operating system to destroy the back office, so small businesses (SMB’s) can do more of what they love. Novo is flipping the script of the FinTech world, and we’re excited to lead the small business FinTech revolution.</span></p>
 <p><span>We are looking for people of character. Pragmatic and capable people who want to see their work drive better outcomes for small businesses — the backbone of our economy. You will join our</span><span> team</span><span> and work on the building blocks of everything Novo ships.</span></p>
 <p><span> </span><span>Why Novo?</span></p>
 <ul>
  <li><span>Novo is a rapidly growing series B fintech startup with a mission-driven team that’s passionate about helping every small business in America</span></li>
  <li><span>Positive, inclusive, supportive culture cheering you on your journey</span></li>
  <li><span>We work with very new technologies and architecture patterns </span></li>
  <li><span>We provide learning and development budgets to help you grow and bond with your team </span></li>
  <li>Able to work from the office 3+ days per week</li>
  <li><span>Offices in NYC, Miami, India, and Colombia</span></li>
 </ul>
</div>
<p>We are seeking a dynamic Senior Recruiter to join our fast-paced team. The ideal candidate will not only excel in sourcing and closing top talent but also embody our culture as a brand ambassador. As a strategic partner to our expanding teams, you will collaborate across various functions, including tech, product, marketing, and operations.</p>
<p>In this role, you will own the full recruitment cycle and be instrumental in developing a scalable, high-impact recruitment engine that attracts diverse, mission-driven talent. A strong understanding of startup culture and fintech hiring dynamics is essential.</p>
<h3><strong>About the Role: <br></strong></h3>
<p>Manage full-cycle recruitment</p>
<ul>
 <li>Manage full-cycle recruitment, from sourcing and attracting talent, screening, interviewing, offer negotiation, to onboarding support.</li>
 <li>Proficient in simultaneously managing multiple requisitions and recruiting initiatives across various domains</li>
 <li>Deep understanding of sourcing platforms, including LinkedIn, GitHub, and AngelList, and sourcing techniques.</li>
 <li>Familiarity with Boolean search, proficient in creative sourcing strategies and passive candidate engagement</li>
 <li>Skilled in closing high-quality candidates within competitive markets</li>
 <li>Successfully recruit and hire top talent within competitive markets</li>
 <li>Familiarity with onboarding workflows and transitions to HR operations team</li>
</ul>
<p>Hiring process design &amp; scalability</p>
<ul>
 <li>Develop competency-based interview frameworks and scorecard-based evaluations</li>
 <li>Training teams on best practices for structured interviews and calibration</li>
 <li>Implement process improvements in high-growth environment</li>
 <li>Utilize automation and AI tools for candidate relationship management, process optimization, and reporting.</li>
</ul>
<p>Data-driven decision making</p>
<ul>
 <li>Using data to drive hiring decisions and evaluate funnel health</li>
 <li>Defining and tracking key recruitment metrics like: Time-to-fill, pipeline conversion, offer acceptance rate, DEI metrics, candidate NPS, quality of hire</li>
 <li>Leverage reports and dashboards to enhance transparency and promote continuous improvement</li>
</ul>
<p>Stakeholder partnership</p>
<ul>
 <li>Build strong relationships with hiring managers and stakeholders across the organization, acting as a trusted advisor and thought leader on recruitment best practices, talent acquisition strategies, and industry trends.</li>
 <li>Balance multiple priorities and hiring manager expectations</li>
 <li>Effectively manage stakeholder expectations and communications throughout the recruitment process. Provide regular updates on recruitment progress and challenges.</li>
 <li>Collaborate closely with hiring managers to understand their requirements, team dynamics, and company culture.</li>
</ul>
<p>Culture champion &amp; brand ambassador</p>
<ul>
 <li>Serve as the face of Novo throughout the hiring process, delivering a candidate experience that reflects our values, mission, and energy.</li>
 <li>Embed culture and DEI principles into hiring conversations, ensuring every candidate interaction upholds and promotes an inclusive environment.</li>
 <li>Partner with internal teams (People, Marketing, Leadership) to elevate employer branding efforts, including campaigns, events, and storytelling initiatives.<strong><br><br></strong></li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>Qualifications</strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>5–6 years of in-house, full-cycle recruiting experience at startups or scale-ups</li>
 <li>Proven track record hiring across multiple business and technical functions</li>
 <li>Experience collaborating directly with senior and executive stakeholders</li>
 <li>Data-informed, highly organized, and outcome-focused</li>
 <li>Advanced sourcing and search capabilities (Boolean, outreach, etc.)</li>
 <li>Proficient in ATS systems (Greenhouse, Lever, SmartRecruiters, AI based new age ATS) and sourcing tools</li>
 <li>Proficient with reporting, analytics dashboards, and hiring funnel metrics</li>
 <li>Resourceful and creative with a bias toward thoughtful, strategic action</li>
 <li>Strong communicator and relationship builder with high integrity and professionalism</li>
 <li>Demonstrated ability to champion company culture and values throughout the hiring process; seen as a culture ambassador who fosters inclusive, values-driven candidate experiences.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Key m</strong><strong>etrics for success</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Fill roles within standard TAT to ensure business continuity and team momentum.</li>
 <li>Launch intake meetings promptly after role approval to accelerate hiring cycles.</li>
 <li>Maintain strong sourcing-to-onsite conversion to reflect top-of-funnel effectiveness.</li>
 <li>Boost outreach response rates using Gem, LinkedIn Recruiter, and personalized messaging.</li>
 <li>Achieve a healthy interview-to-hire ratio to balance selectivity and speed.</li>
 <li>Ensure high candidate NPS to deliver a best-in-class candidate experience.</li>
 <li>Lead process improvements using data and recruiting analytics.</li>
 <li>Earn high satisfaction scores from hiring managers and internal partners.</li>
 <li>Support culture-building initiatives like onboarding, values sessions, and DEI storytelling.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>What’s in it for you:</strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>Compensation: Competitive salary ($150K), meaningful equity.</li>
 <li>Benefits: Premium healthcare, dental, vision, 401(k), generous PTO, and wellness perks</li>
 <li>Location: NYC-based, hybrid role (3+ days work from office mandatory)</li>
 <li>Growth: Join a company in building mode with room to grow your career</li>
 <li>Impact: Help build a recruitment engine and talent brand you will be proud of, from the ground up</li>
</ul>
<div>
 <p><em><span>Novo values diversity as a core tenet of the work we do and the businesses we serve. We are an equal opportunity employer, indiscriminate of race, religion, ethnicity, national origin, citizenship, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, age, veteran status, disability, genetic information or any other protected characteristic. </span></em></p>
</div>');
