INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (478, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/twelve-labs/jobs/48629384-chief-of-staff#content', 'Chief of Staff', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/twelve-labs?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlBlb3BsZSUyMCUyNiUyMEhSIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/a14dd6ae-b109-50eb-b217-502ffb051f00-1746495280', 'Twelve Labs', 'People & HR', 1744156800, '<p><strong>Chief of Staff</strong></p>
<p>At Twelve Labs, we are pioneering the development of frontier multimodal foundation models that can see, hear and understand the world as humans do. Our models have redefined the standards in video-language modeling, allowing developers to build programs with state-of-the-art semantic search, summarization and analysis capabilities.</p>
<p>Twelve Labs has raised $107 million in Seed + Series A funding from world-class VC &amp; corporate partners: NVIDIA, NEA, Radical Ventures, Index Ventures, Snowflake and Databricks. Our advisory team features AI visionaries and founders such as Fei-Fei Li, Silvio Savarese, Alexandr Wang and more. Headquartered in San Francisco, with an influential APAC presence in Seoul, our global footprint underscores our commitment to driving worldwide innovation.</p>
<p><strong>About The Role</strong></p>
<p>We are seeking a highly motivated and strategic Chief of Staff to serve as a right-hand partner to our CEO and executive team at TwelveLabs. The Chief of Staff will drive operational efficiency, oversee key initiatives, and ensure seamless communication across the organization, including Product, Engineering, Sales, and Operations.</p>
<p>This role requires a dynamic leader who can anticipate challenges, foster cross-functional collaboration, and execute high-impact projects that align with our company’s goals. You will be responsible for ensuring that strategic decisions are implemented effectively, helping the organization scale efficiently while maintaining a strong company culture.</p>
<p><strong>In this role, you will provide:</strong></p>
<p><strong>Strategic Leadership</strong>: Partner with the CEO and executive team to set strategic priorities and align them across teams. Act as a thought partner in identifying new business opportunities, improving processes, and resolving complex challenges.<br></p>
<p><strong>Project Management &amp; Execution</strong>: Lead and manage high-priority cross-functional projects, from ideation through execution, ensuring projects are completed on time and within scope.<br></p>
<p><strong>Operational Excellence</strong>: Enhance and streamline business processes, driving continuous improvement across departments. Provide operational support by tracking KPIs, milestones, and deliverables to ensure maximum efficiency.<br></p>
<p><strong>Stakeholder Communication</strong>: Serve as the primary point of contact for internal stakeholders, facilitating clear and transparent communication across teams and departments. Act as a liaison between the CEO and the rest of the organization to ensure alignment and execution of the company\'s vision.<br></p>
<p><strong>Problem-Solving &amp; Decision Support</strong>: Anticipate potential obstacles and proactively provide solutions that align with the organization’s strategic goals. Analyze data to provide actionable insights that aid decision-making.<br></p>
<p><strong>Cross-Functional Collaboration</strong>: Foster a culture of collaboration, driving alignment across different teams. Work closely with the leadership teams from <strong>Product, Engineering, Sales, and Operations</strong> to ensure that business goals are met effectively and efficiently.<br></p>
<p><strong>Ad-Hoc Leadership</strong>: Take on special projects or initiatives, including handling sensitive, high-stakes situations, while supporting the CEO in their executive duties as required.</p>
<p><strong>You may be a good fit if you have:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p>6+ years of experience in strategy, consulting, product, program management or a similar leadership role.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Exceptional problem-solving and analytical skills.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Strong ability to manage multiple projects and prioritize effectively.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Outstanding communication and interpersonal skills.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Experience working in a fast-paced and dynamic environment.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>High emotional intelligence and ability to build trusted relationships.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Proficiency in business software, including project management tools and data analysis platforms.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Even if there are a few checkboxes that aren’t ticked through your prior experience, we still encourage you to apply! If you are a 0-1 achiever, a ferocious learner, and a kind and fun team player who motivates others, you will find a home at Twelve Labs.</p>
<p>We are a global company that values the uniqueness of each person’s journey. It is the differences in our cultural, educational, and life experiences that allow us to constantly challenge the status quo. We are looking for individuals who are motivated by our mission and eager to make an impact as we push the bounds of technology to transform the world. Join us as we revolutionize video understanding and multimodal AI.</p>
<p><br><strong>Benefits and Perks</strong></p>
<p>🤝 An open and inclusive culture and work environment.</p>
<p>🧑‍💻 Work closely with a collaborative, mission-driven team on cutting-edge AI technology.</p>
<p>🦷 Full health, dental, and vision benefits.</p>
<p>✈️ Flexible PTO and parental leave policy. Office closed the week of Christmas and New Years.</p>
<p>🏙 Remote-flexible, offices in San Francisco and Seoul and coworking stipend.</p>
<p>🛂 VISA support (such as H1B and OPT transfer for US employees).</p>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (479, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline/jobs/48393366-fulfillment-supervisor-contract#content', 'Fulfillment Supervisor - Contract', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/zipline?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlBlb3BsZSUyMCUyNiUyMEhSIl19#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/716c870c-b07d-50ff-ab75-427af872bf20-1740432205', 'Zipline', 'People & HR', 1743724800, '<h3><strong>About Zipline</strong></h3>
<p>Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building the first instant logistics system that serves all humans equally. Leveraging expertise in robotics and autonomy, Zipline serves tens of millions of people around the world.</p>
<p>Join Zipline and help us to make good on our promise to build an equitable and more resilient global supply chain for billions of people.</p>
<h3><strong>About You and The Role </strong></h3>
<p>The Zipline Operations team is looking for a Fulfillment Operations Coordinator to support our fulfillment operations in the greater Dallas - Fort Worth areas and the ideal candidate for this role is a motivated and experienced individual that excels in fast-paced, physical environments, and is excited to roll up their sleeves. In this role, own the day-to-day fulfillment operations of 3-5 Walmart Supercenters, ensuring the site processes run smoothly, efficiently and safely. You will be responsible for ensuring your locations meet performance metrics and identify opportunities to improve our operating processes.</p>
<p><strong>This is an onsite role and candidates must reside in the greater Dallas Fort-Worth area and be willing to travel around the metroplex as needed.</strong></p>
<h3><strong>What You\'ll Do </strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>Lead a high-performing team of Fulfillment Operators across multiple sites. Set your team up for success to work safely and productively. You’ll partner with Flight and Customer Operations to effectively support daily tasks and ensure high performance of your team.</li>
 <li>You will own the day-to-day operations of one of our fulfillment operations, ensuring the site processes run smoothly, efficiently and safely.</li>
 <li>You’ll own scheduling and managing a labor budget. You will be responsible for ensuring your site meets performance metric goals.</li>
 <li>Ensure your teams are providing our customers with the best possible experience on each and every order. You will be responsible for maintaining key quality metrics including order accuracy and fulfillment speed.</li>
 <li>Use data to identify pain-points or areas of inefficiency within our current processes. Design, build and execute process improvement projects to improve our fulfillment operations, quality metrics, and the employee experience.</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>What You\'ll Bring </strong></h3>
<ul>
 <li>You\'re self-motivated, positive, and a team player</li>
 <li>You have 2+ years’ experience: In Operations, Warehouse Logistics, Retail Management, Fulfillment, or related field</li>
 <li>Willingness to operate in a fast-changing environment and make adjustments when</li>
 <li>You\'re able to be on your feet and handle warehouse duties including lifting up to 5 pounds (with or without accommodations).</li>
 <li>Must successfully pass a background check, drug test and E-Verification</li>
</ul>
<h3><strong>What Else You Need to Know </strong></h3>
<p>Zipline is an equal opportunity employer and prohibits discrimination and harassment of any type without regard to race, color, ancestry, national origin, religion or religious creed, mental or physical disability, medical condition, genetic information, sex (including pregnancy, childbirth, and related medical conditions), sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, marital status, military or veteran status, citizenship, or other characteristics protected by state, federal or local law or our other policies.</p>
<p>We value diversity at Zipline and welcome applications from those who are traditionally underrepresented in tech. If you like the sound of this position but are not sure if you are the perfect fit, please apply!</p>
<p>Targeted comp: $31-$32 / hour + benefits</p>');
