INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (481, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/artera-2-45603da9-8558-41e0-8432-f493987a2c76/jobs/52811599-product-manager#content', 'Product Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/artera-2-45603da9-8558-41e0-8432-f493987a2c76?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlByb2R1Y3QiXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/a085e5e1-a10c-51c0-a4f8-6edbcd7e9142-1748136900', 'Artera', 'Product', 1750204800, '<section>
 <div>
  <b>ABOUT ARTERA</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Our Mission: </b><span>Make healthcare #1 in customer service.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>What We Deliver: </b><span>Artera, a SaaS leader in digital health, transforms patient experience with AI-powered virtual agents (voice and text) for every step of the patient journey. Artera’s virtual agents support front desk staff to improve patient access including self-scheduling, intake, forms, billing and more. Whether augmenting a team or unleashing a fully autonomous digital workforce, Artera offers multiple virtual agent options to meet healthcare organizations where they are in their AI journey. Artera helps support 2B communications in 109 languages across voice, text and web. A decade of healthcare expertise, powered by AI.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Our Impact:</b><span> Trusted by 900+ provider organizations — including specialty groups, FQHCs, large IDNs and federal agencies — engaging 100 million patients annually. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Our award-winning culture: </b><span>Since founding in 2015, Artera has consistently been recognized for its innovative technology, business growth, and named a top place to work. Examples of these accolades include: </span><b>Inc. 5000 Fastest Growing Private Companies</b><span> (2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024); </span><b>Deloitte Technology Fast 500</b><span> (2021, 2022, 2023, 2024); </span><b>Built In Best Companies to Work For</b><span> (2021, 2022, 2023, 2024, 2025). Artera has also been recognized by Forbes as one of “America’s Best Startup Employers,” Newsweek as one of the “World’s Best Digital Health Companies,” and named one of the top “44 Startups to Bet your Career on in 2024” by Business Insider. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Summary</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  We\'re seeking a highly motivated and experienced <b>Product Manager</b> to join our team and drive an existing product to General Availability (GA). This is a critical role that will own the completion and successful launch of a key offering, followed by defining the future roadmap, including integrating patient preferences into our AI agent workflows. If you\'re a results-oriented leader who thrives in a fast-paced environment and excels at bringing products to market, we want to hear from you.
 </div>
 <div>
  This <b>Product Manager</b> will be instrumental in the final push to GA, meticulously managing the product backlog and ensuring seamless execution. You\'ll be the central hub for communication, providing crucial updates to stakeholders, leading key meetings, and ensuring all teams are aligned on priorities. Your day-to-day will involve a high degree of collaboration, not only with our internal engineering and design teams but also with our knowledge and customer support teams, contributing to customer webinars and knowledge base content. You\'ll also be responsible for proactively identifying and escalating risks, ensuring that important information cuts through the noise and reaches the right people. Post-launch, you\'ll pivot to strategic planning, defining how patient preferences can be integrated into our innovative AI agent workflows, charting the course for the product\'s next evolution.
 </div>
 <div>
  This position will report to our Senior Director, Product Management. Some of the key stakeholders are based in Hungary, so there is a requirement to work Eastern time zone for the best opportunities for collaboration.
 </div>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Responsibilities</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Drive an existing software product to General Availability (GA), overseeing all remaining development, testing, and launch activities.</li>
  <li>Define and build a V1 roadmap for patient preferences and their integration into AI agent workflows.</li>
  <li>Manage and groom the product backlog to ensure clear priorities and efficient development cycles.</li>
  <li>Communicate critical project updates to all stakeholders, ensuring transparency and alignment.</li>
  <li>Lead and facilitate stakeholder meetings to gather feedback, address concerns, and drive decisions.</li>
  <li>Support knowledge and customer-facing teams by contributing to customer webinars and knowledge base content.</li>
  <li>Communicate top-down priorities effectively to the development teams.</li>
  <li>Proactively identify and raise risks upwards, ensuring timely awareness and mitigation strategies.</li>
  <li>Maintain bi-directional communication flow, ensuring information is shared effectively across all levels and teams.</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Requirements</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Proven success in taking a software project from discovery through General Availability (GA), with the ability to articulate the detailed process followed.</li>
  <li>Experience in a B2B2C setting is highly desirable.</li>
  <li>Direct experience working with AI products and engineering teams.</li>
  <li>Proficiency with communication platforms and tools.</li>
  <li>Expertise with Jira and Confluence (Atlassian Suite) for project and documentation management.</li>
  <li>Demonstrated autonomy and the ability to independently solve complex problems.</li>
  <li>Exceptional written and verbal communication skills.</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <h3>Bonus</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Prior experience in Healthcare IT or knowledge of the healthcare market.</li>
  <li>Prior experience with product marketing or involvement in the product marketing process</li>
  <li>Familiarity with Figma for design collaboration.</li>
  <li>Strong project management skills.</li>
  <li>Scrum Master certification.</li>
  <li>Atlassian Certified Professional designation.</li>
 </ul>
</section>
<section>
 <div>
  <b>OUR APPROACH TO WORK LOCATION</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Artera has hybrid office locations in Santa Barbara, CA, and Philadelphia (Wayne), PA, where team members typically come in three days a week. Specific frequency can vary depending on your team\'s needs, manager expectations and/or role responsibilities.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>In addition to our U.S. office locations, we are intentionally building </span><b><span>geographically concentrated</span></b><span> teams in several key metropolitan areas, which we call our “</span><b><span>Hiring Hubs</span></b><span>.” We are currently hiring remote candidates located within the following hiring hubs:</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>- Boston Metro Area, MA</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>- Chicago Metro Area, IL</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>- Denver Metro Area, CO</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>- Kansas City Metro Area (KS/MO)</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>- Los Angeles Metro Area, CA</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>- San Francisco / Bay Area, CA</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>- Seattle Metro Area, WA</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>This hub-based model helps us cultivate strong local connections and team cohesion, even in a distributed environment. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>To be eligible for employment at Artera, candidates must reside in one of our hybrid office cities or one of the designated hiring hubs. Specific roles may call out location preferences when relevant.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>As our hubs grow, we may establish local offices to further enhance in-person connection and collaboration. </span><b><span>While there are no current plans in place</span></b><span>, should an office open in your area, we anticipate implementing a hybrid model. Any future attendance expectations would be developed thoughtfully, considering factors like typical commute times and access to public transit, to ensure they are fair and practical for the local team.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>WORKING AT ARTERA </b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Company benefits</b><span> - Full health benefits (medical, dental, and vision), flexible spending accounts, company paid life insurance, company paid short-term &amp; long-term disability, company equity, voluntary benefits, 401(k) and more! </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Career development</b><span> - Manager development cohorts, employee development funds</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Generous time off</b><span> - Company holidays, Winter &amp; Summer break, and flexible time off</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>Employee Resource Groups (ERGs)</b><span> - We believe that everyone should belong at their workplace. Our ERGs are available for identifying employees or allies to join. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>EQUAL EMPLOYMENT OPPORTUNITY (EEO) STATEMENT</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Artera is an Equal Opportunity Employer and is committed to fair and equitable hiring practices. All hiring decisions at Artera are based on strategic business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications. All candidates are considered without regard to race, color, religion, gender, sexuality, national origin, age, disability, genetics or any other protected status. </span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Artera is committed to providing employees with a work environment free of discrimination and harassment; Artera will not tolerate discrimination or harassment of any kind.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Artera provides reasonable accommodations for applicants and employees in compliance with state and federal laws. If you need an accommodation, please reach out to hr@artera.io.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <b>DATA PRIVACY</b>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>Artera values your privacy. By submitting your application, you consent to the processing of your personal information provided in conjunction with your application. For more information please refer to our </span><a href="https://artera.io/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a><span>.</span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span><b>SECURITY REQUIREMENTS</b></span>
 </div>
 <div>
  <span>All employees are responsible for protecting the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of the organization’s systems and data, including safeguarding Artera’s sensitive information such as, Personal identifiable Information (PII) and Protected Health Information (PHI). Those with specific security or privacy responsibilities must ensure compliance with organizational policies, regulatory requirements, and applicable standards and frameworks by implementing safeguards, monitoring for threats, reporting incidents, and addressing data handling risks or breaches.</span>
 </div>
</section>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (482, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/madkudu/jobs/52801113-junior-product-manager#content', 'Junior Product Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/madkudu?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlByb2R1Y3QiXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/e9a791e1-f36f-5596-b54d-252f966da424-1748914582', 'MadKudu', 'Product', 1750204800, '<div>
 <p>MadKudu is the one-stop shop for B2B Saas companies who want to optimize their Revenue automation game. Madkudu translates buyer signals (1st &amp; 3rd party data) into automated actions to generate more pipeline.</p>
 <p>We are a tech startup based in San Francisco, CA. We raised $30m from some of the best VCs in the world (Felicis, BGV, Alven), have revenue, and amazing customers (Figma, MongoDB, Unity, etc.).<br></p>
 <p>Delivering the right products to our customers is the heart of what we do, and we need your help to keep the momentum going. Did we mention some of our clients include MongoDB, LucidChart, Udemy, and other big names you probably know? You\'ll be shaping the future for them too.<br><br>
  This is a<strong> 6-month intership position</strong> in <strong><u>San Francisco, CA</u> </strong>with the possibility of a permanent role if it’s a good fit. We support <strong>J-1 visa sponsorship</strong> for recent grads from France who want to gain international experience in tech. <br><br>
  This is an entry-level position perfect for recent graduates or those with internship experience in consulting or product development. We value curiosity, customer obsession, and a builder\'s mindset!<br></p>
 <h3>What You’ll Do:</h3>
 <ul>
  <li>Identify product improvements using data from web analytics, customer feedback, and other sources</li>
  <li>Collaborate with engineers to ensure smooth functionality</li>
  <li>Brainstorm and develop new product ideas</li>
  <li>Partner with Product Managers and stakeholders to help bring products to life</li>
  <li>Conduct customer discovery and gather insights</li>
  <li>Define product requirements and help guide ideation</li>
  <li>Test products and features to ensure top-notch quality</li>
  <li>Perform market analysis to stay ahead of trends</li>
 </ul>
 <h3><strong>What You’ll Need:</strong></h3>
 <ul>
  <li>A bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, or a related field (Master Degree is a plus)</li>
  <li>Proficiency in Python and SQL</li>
  <li>Excellent communication skills, both verbal and written</li>
  <li>Strong time management and multitasking abilities</li>
  <li>Creativity and a knack for thinking outside the box</li>
  <li>A passion for data and making informed decisions based on analytics</li>
  <li>Strong interest in AI</li>
 </ul>
 <h3><strong>Who We Are:</strong></h3>
 <p>Founded in 2015, MadKudu is on a mission to solve one of today’s toughest challenges: achieving relevance at scale. We empower B2B marketing and sales teams to make sharp, data-driven decisions that shape the customer journey—whether it\'s prioritizing high-revenue prospects or automating forms that direct leads to the “fast lane.”</p>
 <p>Our co-founders, Sam Levan (CEO) and Francis Brero (CRO), are data experts with 25+ years of combined experience in predictive analytics. Together, they’re transforming the way SaaS companies use data to make smarter decisions.</p>
 <p>With $18M raised in our Series A, we’re backed by top investors like Felicis, Alven, and Techstars, along with leaders like Elena Verna (ex-CMO at Miro). And we’re just getting started!<br></p>
 <p>Ready to dive into some of the most exciting data challenges out there? Apply now, or reach out to our recruiter, Ruben Hernandez, with any questions</p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (483, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/rezilient-health/jobs/52762374-product-quality-assurance-specialist#content', 'Product Quality Assurance Specialist', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/rezilient-health?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlByb2R1Y3QiXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/4f876ff2-c49a-5ffb-a55e-7fd85ac4f7c8-1748881345', 'Rezilient Health', 'Product', 1750118400, '<p>At Rezilient Health, we’re not telehealth and we’re not your typical doctor’s office — we’re the best of both worlds, redefining how primary care is delivered.</p>
<p>To make that vision possible, our engineering team builds and maintains the custom tools that power our care model. Our technology is mission-critical, and we take pride in supporting a fast-evolving operation that serves real people with real health needs.</p>
<p>As a Product QA Specialist, you will be the connection between product development and the rest of the organization. You’ll work closely with Engineering, Clinical Operations, and Customer Success teams to ensure our product ecosystem is clearly documented, well-understood, and continuously improving. You’ll play a central role in maintaining internal knowledge systems, fielding and prioritizing feedback, and helping the team implement product enhancements efficiently and transparently.</p>
<p>This role is ideal for someone who thrives at the intersection of product, process, and people. You are highly organized, proactive, and an excellent communicator. You love building systems that bring structure to complexity. You’re energized by the opportunity to wear many hats, take ownership of your work, and help teams function more effectively through process improvement and thoughtful documentation.</p>
<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>Cross-Functional Collaboration &amp; Communication</p>
<ul>
 <li>Act as the primary liaison between the Engineering team and other departments (Clinical, Sales, Operations), ensuring seamless communication on product updates, issues, and feature releases.</li>
 <li>Translate technical concepts and product changes into accessible language and formats for non-technical stakeholders.</li>
</ul>
<p>Documentation &amp; Training</p>
<ul>
 <li>Develop and maintain comprehensive internal documentation (e.g., FAQs, step-by-step guides, onboarding materials) and training videos for internal teams using our custom software, EMR, and operational tools.</li>
 <li>Create and manage external-facing product documentation and self-help resources (e.g., support articles, video walk-throughs, troubleshooting guides).</li>
 <li>Draft and publish release notes, product feature summaries, and “what’s new” videos to support internal product launches and updates.</li>
</ul>
<p>Product Operations &amp; Process Management</p>
<ul>
 <li>Implement and maintain streamlined systems for bug tracking, feature suggestion intake, and issue resolution; ensure timely triage and follow-through with the Engineering team.</li>
 <li>Develop workflows and tools to prioritize, define, and route feature requests from across the organization.</li>
 <li>Own and update the internal product feature matrix, including a detailed breakdown of features, user permissions, and access by role type.</li>
 <li>Maintain clinical workflow diagrams in collaboration with the Clinical team, and identify opportunities to optimize processes via technology.</li>
</ul>
<p>Quality Assurance &amp; Compliance</p>
<ul>
 <li>Coordinate and execute QA testing for new releases, ensuring functionality, usability, and adherence to security and compliance standards.</li>
 <li>Maintain dashboards and documentation pertaining to engineering and IT compliance, including task tracking, remediation status, and audits.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Bachelor’s Degree or equivalent work experience in Product Operations, Health Tech, or Engineering Support.</li>
 <li>Highly organized, with a keen eye for detail and a passion for process optimization.</li>
 <li>Proven ability to manage multiple projects and deadlines in a fast-paced, startup environment.</li>
 <li>Strong communication skills, both written and verbal.</li>
 <li>Experience producing clear and engaging content for diverse audiences.</li>
 <li>Comfortable working with minimal structure and shaping new systems from the ground up.</li>
 <li>Familiarity with modern workflow and documentation tools including: Google Workspace, Lucidchart, Miro, Notion, Jira, and Zapier.</li>
 <li>Experience working in a clinical or health tech environment.</li>
 <li>Knowledge of security and compliance frameworks (HIPAA, SOC 2, etc.).</li>
 <li>Prior experience in QA testing or technical documentation.</li>
 <li>Familiarity with EMR systems or healthcare operations workflows.</li>
</ul>
<p>This opportunity offers the chance to shape the future of healthcare in a culture where your ideas and contributions have a meaningful impact on the organization\'s future. You’ll be part of a supportive, collaborative, and diverse team, with competitive compensation and benefits that include generous PTO, paid family leave, comprehensive medical, dental, vision, and life insurance, as well as stock options.</p>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (484, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/self-2/jobs/52755646-principal-product-manager#content', 'Principal Product Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/self-2?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlByb2R1Y3QiXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/37ab5577-f020-5034-875b-9f37f7a54864-1748050325', 'Self', 'Product', 1750118400, '<div>
 <p><span>Self Financial is a venture-backed, high-growth FinTech company with a mission to increase economic inclusion and financial resilience by empowering people to build credit and build savings.</span></p>
 <p><span>We\'re looking for people who share our passion and are driven to tackle challenges, find solutions and make the financial space better for the communities we serve.</span></p>
 <p><span>Our team is passionate about challenging the status quo of the credit industry by providing people accessible tools to take control of their credit. Executing on our mission requires deep collaboration across our teams to ensure our products reach the people who can benefit from them the most, particularly the 100 million+ Americans who have no or low credit.</span></p>
 <p><span>We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. To that end, we seek to recruit, develop and retain the most talented people from a diverse candidate pool. </span></p>
</div>
<p><strong>Who You Are:</strong></p>
<p>You are a product leader who moves fluidly between strategy and execution. You dive deep into the product, protect the team’s focus, and build a clear vision that aligns with customer needs and business goals. You don’t just ship features, you craft intentional iterations, observe outcomes, and scale what works. You\'re known for making smart trade-offs, advocating for the customer, and driving momentum across complex, cross-functional initiatives.</p>
<p>You possess strong technical fluency, enabling you to collaborate effectively with engineering on how the product is built (not just what it does) ensuring long-term scalability. You\'re equally comfortable inspiring a team to do their best work and making hard decisions when trade-offs are necessary.</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>About the Role:</strong></p>
<p>As Principal Product Manager, you’ll lead strategic initiatives within our Borrow &amp; Spend line, improving core experiences, shaping new offerings, and stewarding a product vision rooted in customer success. You’ll operate across a broad surface area, from early-stage concepts to iterative launches, with a focus on delivering high-impact results and durable infrastructure.</p>
<p>You’ll work closely with stakeholders across engineering, compliance, risk, analytics,operations, design, and marketing to ensure alignment and execution excellence.</p>
<p><strong>What You Will Do:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Define and evolve the product strategy for the Borrow &amp; Spend portfolio, with a focus on sustainable credit building and customer empowerment.</li>
 <li>Lead product discovery, iteration planning, and launches — balancing incremental experiments with big bets.</li>
 <li>Champion a customer-first mindset through qualitative and quantitative insights, a/b testing, and usability validation.</li>
 <li>Act as a thought partner to engineering — shaping how features are architected to support long-term platform goals.</li>
 <li>Manage multiple concurrent initiatives across different stages, from scoping to execution to rollout.</li>
 <li>Inspire teams to stay focused, make tough trade-offs, and ship high-quality work at pace.</li>
 <li>Communicate product strategy, vision, and outcomes to executives and stakeholders with clarity and influence.</li>
 <li>Maintain deep subject matter expertise in our card products, compliance requirements, and market positioning.</li>
 <li>Maintain an awareness of major industry trends, competitive feature landscape and developing appropriate prioritization</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p><strong>What You Bring:</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>7–10+ years of product management experience, with recent leadership in complex or regulated product domains.</li>
 <li>Experience owning a product end-to-end, from vision and roadmap to launch and iteration.</li>
 <li>A track record of influencing across disciplines and levels, with clear and persuasive communication.</li>
 <li>Strong analytical skills and fluency with both data (SQL a plus) and qualitative research methods.</li>
 <li>Technical fluency — you understand how systems fit together and speak the language of engineers.</li>
 <li>Experience in credit, lending, or financial infrastructure is strongly preferred.</li>
 <li>A deep sense of ownership and commitment to Self’s mission of building economic inclusion.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><em>Base salary range: $142,000-190,000 annually. Individual pay is based on factors unique to each candidate, including skill set, experience, and other job-related reasons.</em></strong></p>
<div>
 <h4><strong>Benefits and Perks:</strong></h4>
 <p><span>We have the compensation and benefits you expect. But there\'s one thing that Self Financial can offer that many companies cannot: we can positively change the world, while making a profit. We are a team of Builders, empowering our customers to build their dreams. We have a Do the Right Thing ethos in all that we do, and we hope you value that approach, too. </span></p>
 <p><strong>Our perks include:</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li><span>Company equity in the form of Stock Options</span></li>
  <li><span>Performance-based bonuses</span></li>
  <li><span>Generous employer-paid health, vision and dental insurance coverage</span></li>
  <li><span>Flexible vacation policy</span></li>
  <li><span>Educational assistance</span></li>
  <li><span>Free gym membership</span></li>
  <li><span>Casual dress code</span></li>
  <li><span>Team building events and activities</span></li>
  <li><span>Remote work arrangements/ flexible work schedule</span></li>
  <li><span>Paid parental leave </span></li>
 </ul>
 <p><span>Self Financial requires all employees hired to successfully pass a background check.</span></p>
 <p><span>We are an Equal Opportunity Employer.</span></p>
 <p><em><strong>At this time, we are only able to consider applicants who are U.S. Citizens or Green Card Holders for employment opportunities. We appreciate your understanding.</strong></em></p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (485, 'https://jobs.techstars.comhttps://vanhack.com/job/11425?utm_source=Techstars+job+board&utm_medium=getro.com&gh_src=Techstars+job+board', 'Product Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/vanhack?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlByb2R1Y3QiXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/0908ecb7-238e-5c57-b010-b90918f3ddc5-1748828576', 'VanHack', 'Product', 1750118400, null);
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (486, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/openly-com/jobs/52583387-senior-director-claims-product-management-remote-us#content', 'Senior Director, Claims Product Management (Remote, US)', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/openly-com?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlByb2R1Y3QiXX0%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/abc27225-9040-5fc0-b719-90af7954754c-1746150104', 'Openly', 'Product', 1749772800, '<div>
 <h2><span></span></h2>
 <h2><span>Why Openly</span></h2>
 <p><span>Openly is rebuilding insurance from the ground up. We are re-envisioning and enhancing every aspect of the customer experience. Doing this requires a rapidly growing team of exceptional, curious, empathetic people with a wide range of skill sets, spanning technology, data science, product, marketing, sales, service, claims handling, finance, etc. </span></p>
 <h2><span>The Openly Difference</span></h2>
 <p><span>We created Openly because we saw an evident gap in the market for premium insurance made simple. Consumers deserve more complete coverage at competitive prices. </span></p>
 <ul>
  <li><span><span><strong>The Price Difference</strong>: </span>Using cutting-edge data and technology, we provide you with customizable, competitive prices to protect your most valuable assets.</span></li>
  <li><span><strong><span>The Policy Difference:</span></strong> Coverages are truly customizable to meet your individual protection needs, for both standard coverages and optional add-ons.</span></li>
  <li><span><span><strong>The Experience Difference:</strong></span> From tailored claims handling to highly responsive customer service, we are focused on making the home insurance purchasing process a better overall experience.</span></li>
 </ul>
 <h2><span>Welcome to your next adventure.</span></h2>
 <p>At Openly, our people are just as important as our product. For us, collaboration, communication, and work-life balance are more than nice-to-haves— they’re the must-haves that make us who we are. We believe a great company is the result of a shared set of values, so we look for these qualities in every candidate we hire.</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Integrity</li>
  <li>Empathy</li>
  <li>Teamwork</li>
