     <h4><span>Job description</span></h4>
     <div>
      <div>
       <div>
        <p>Wakeo provides a SaaS platform to bring real-time visibility on intercontinental transportation.</p>
        <p>Using AI-based technology, we help shippers and logistics providers build a resilient and sustainable supply chain 🌍</p>
        <p>We already work with global leaders such as Uniqlo, Michelin, Corteva, Air Liquide, Rhenus or Hartrodt with users in more than 180 countries and we are rapidly growing our network.</p>
        <p>And we do not plan to stop there! We raised €30 million with Statkraft Ventures and our historical investors Promus Ventures, 360 Capital, 50 Partners and Techstars, to give even more visibility to worldwide transport actors. 🚀<br></p>
        <h3><strong>MISSIONS 💪</strong></h3>
        <p>As a <strong>Senior Product Manager</strong>, your mission is to maximize the impact of your squad by building products that deliver real value to our customers &amp; prospects. You own the product lifecycle end-to-end, from identifying the right problems, running the discovery phase and delivering the value to our clients (including the go-to-market).</p>
        <p><strong>Product strategy &amp; vision</strong></p>
        <ul>
         <li>Own and drive the squad’s roadmap in line with company OKRs, market shifts, and user pain points.</li>
         <li>Translate market intelligence, customer insights, and competitive dynamics into product bets.</li>
         <li>Collaborate closely with leadership and cross-functional teams to align vision, priorities, and execution.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Product discovery &amp; problem solving</strong></p>
        <ul>
         <li>Lead discovery with a bias toward action (structured interviews with clients, market &amp; behavior analysis, POCs).</li>
         <li>Partner with Sales, CS, and Ops to deeply understand user pain and business constraints.</li>
         <li>Validate and de-risk product opportunities before prioritizing the roadmap and committing engineering resources.</li>
         <li>Test AI features on a daily basis to learn how it would change your job and squad scope tomorrow.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Product delivery &amp; go-to-market</strong></p>
        <ul>
         <li>Define the specs and the UX/UI for both API &amp; the web app.</li>
         <li>Work hand-in-hand with engineers to ship high-quality features quickly and iteratively.</li>
         <li>Drive delivery by managing the backlog, refining specs, and facilitating agile rituals.</li>
         <li>Proactively remove blockers and continuously improve team workflows and rituals.</li>
         <li>Design the go-to-market strategy and push for the adoption of new releases.</li>
         <li>Track adoption and impact of features shipped, and iterate based on feedback and data.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3><strong>IDEAL PROFILE ⭐</strong></h3>
        <p>You’re a strategic thinker &amp; problem solver, with a strong product sense, a technical edge, and a bias for action. You are generalist, from A to Z (design, product marketing, tech, client-facing, etc.), know how to navigate complexity, align stakeholders, and deliver value to users.</p>
        <ul>
         <li><strong>Languages</strong>: You’re fluent in <strong>French and English</strong>, both spoken and written.</li>
         <li><strong>Experience</strong>: You have 5+ years of hands-on Product Management experience, ideally in an international <strong>B2B SaaS</strong> company. You\'ve owned significant product scopes and delivered in fast-paced, high-expectation environments.</li>
         <li><strong>Technical &amp; analytical skills</strong>: You have a technical or analytical background that makes you comfortable with figures and data analysis. You’re comfortable discussing APIs, integration with partners/third-parties, or technical trade-offs with engineers.</li>
         <li><strong>Business acumen</strong>: You understand the business impact of product decisions and think in terms of customer value, ROI, and scalability. You have a clear sense of prioritization and are able to drive focus in a sea of competing demands.</li>
         <li><strong>Communication &amp; influence</strong>: You’re clear, structured, and straight-forward in your communication. You love to collect insights from everyone and know how to align stakeholders.</li>
         <li><strong>Execution in ambiguity</strong>: You thrive in complexity and don’t wait for perfect clarity. You break down problems into small pieces, set direction, and bring cross-functional teams along with you.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3><strong>Why joining us :</strong></h3>
        <p>Wakeo is the perfect company if you want to :</p>
        <ul>
         <li>Live the start-up adventure in a fast-growing environment within a massive industry with almost limitless opportunities.</li>
