 <p><b>The Position:</b></p>
 <p>We are looking to hire an energetic and fun-loving Soccer + Sports Coach! Who will lead our children in fun and educational activities while ensuring safety for all. Our ideal candidate has prior experience working with children (as a sports coach, teacher, camper or leader), and enjoys working with children. This position is excellent for someone who has an interest in pursuing early childhood education, or child development. New Coaches can work 5-25 classes a week and can earn from $20 per hr up to $45 per hr.</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Our Coaches use individual attention to ensure every child has success.</li>
  <li>Our Coaches use a non-competitive approach to ensure classes are fun with a stress-free environment.</li>
  <li>Our Coaches use positive reinforcement to encourage children to do better and celebrate success.</li>
  <li>And finally, our coaches have a blast. They are open-minded, and know that coaching is a continuous journey. All Coaches are open to feedback and strive to be better by attending regular trainings and following the Super Soccer Stars Coaching Manual.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Qualifications:</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Experience working with children 5 years and under.</li>
  <li>Expressive, charismatic, and nurturing personality.</li>
  <li>Responsible, reliable, punctual, dedicated, and confident individuals.</li>
  <li>HIGH ENERGY!</li>
  <li>Comfort with managing groups of children and adults.</li>
  <li>Ability to follow Super Soccer Stars curriculum and tailor lessons to specific developmental levels.</li>
  <li>Experience working with non-neurotypical children is a huge PLUS.</li>
  <li>Availability must include the following: Tuesday and Thursday Mornings (9 am – 12 pm), Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday Afternoons (2 pm – 6 pm), and a Weekend morning (8:30 am – 2 pm).</li>
  <li>Punctual, willing to learn and accept feedback.</li>
  <li>Must be motivated, energetic, patient, and attentive.</li>
  <li>Hands-on, dynamic, and outgoing.</li>
  <li>Reliable access to a vehicle.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>Benefits:</b></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Competitive Compensation.</li>
  <li>Caring and proactive team environment with room to grow.</li>
  <li>Reimbursement on license and credentials you obtain while working with us upon approval.</li>
  <li>Paid Trainings.</li>
  <li>Bonuses.</li>
 </ul>
</div>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (628, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/coachcorner-2/jobs/52763927-the-baseball-center-instructor#content', 'The Baseball Center Instructor', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/coachcorner-2#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/f9374990-3cca-51f1-ba04-e0e1b8b4aeb8-1748881088', 'CoachCorner', 'Quality Assurance', 1750118400, '<div>
 <p>The Baseball Center Nyc<br>
   New York, NY</p>
 <div>
  <p><strong>About the position</strong></p>
  <p>The Baseball Center NYC (TBCNYC) is dedicated to fostering a positive environment for players of all ages and skill levels, focusing on their development both on and off the field. The mission of TBCNYC is to cultivate quality recreational, travel ball, and high school baseball players through well-structured practice plans and a strong belief in the players’ potential. The organization expects its staff to exemplify punctuality, preparedness, and the behaviors necessary for success in baseball. As an Instructor &amp; Coach at TBCNYC, you will be responsible for providing private, group, and team baseball instruction in alignment with the center’s mission and business strategy. This role involves designing, documenting, and presenting practice plans, game day rosters, and depth charts, as well as creating individual profiles for private lessons. Clear communication of practice and game details with assigned teams and clients is essential. You may also assume the role of Head or Assistant Coach for any team, which includes leading practices and games or tournaments. In addition to coaching responsibilities, you will assist in maintaining the TBCNYC facility, which includes tasks such as keeping the coaches’ lounge clean, setting up and cleaning the training cage, and managing pro-shop sales and inventory. You will also play a role in recruiting and providing instruction to players in the NYC Stars “Farm System” and the NYC Rising Stars Travel Prep Program. Adherence to TBCNYC schedules is crucial, and you should be prepared for potential travel within the Tri-State and East Coast regions, as well as weekend shifts based on facility and league assignments. Proficiency in Microsoft Office, particularly Excel and Word, is required, along with familiarity with tools like Blast Motion, Hit Trax, and Hudl Technique. A Bachelor’s degree is preferred, along with at least two years of coaching experience in recreational, travel, or middle/high school baseball.</p>
 </div>
 <div>
  <p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
  <ul>
   <li>Provide private, group, and team baseball instruction in alignment with TBCNYC’s mission.</li>
   <li>Design, document, and present practice plans, game day rosters, and depth charts.</li>
   <li>Communicate clear and precise practice and game details with assigned teams and clients.</li>
   <li>Assume the position of Head or Assistant Coach for any team at any time, including practices and games/tournaments.</li>
   <li>Assist or lead activities required to maintain TBCNYC’s facility, including cleanliness and organization.</li>
   <li>Assist or lead activities for any TBCNYC program, lesson, and/or camp.</li>
   <li>Recruit and offer insight/instruction to players in the NYC Stars ‘Farm System’ and the NYC Rising Stars Travel Prep Program.</li>
   <li>Adhere to TBCNYC schedules, being prompt and prepared for each practice, game, lesson, and/or camp.</li>
  </ul>
 </div>
 <div>
  <p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
  <ul>
   <li>Bachelor’s degree preferred.</li>
   <li>Two plus years of coaching experience for recreational, travel, or middle/high school baseball.</li>
   <li>Current proficiency with Microsoft Office, particularly Excel and Word.</li>
   <li>Past use and understanding of Blast Motion, Hit Trax, and/or Hudl Technique.</li>
  </ul>
 </div>
 <div>
  <p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>
  <ul>
   <li>Hourly salary of $20 – $25</li>
   <li>Bonus/Commission opportunities</li>
  </ul>
 </div>
</div>');
