   <h2><strong>Head of Channel &amp; Partnerships</strong></h2>
   <p><strong>Location:</strong> Salt Lake City, Utah <strong>or</strong> Belfast, Northern Ireland</p>
   <p><strong>Reports to:</strong> VP Revenue | Works closely with CTO and VP Marketing and</p>
   <p><strong>Role type:</strong> Full-time, permanent<br></p>
   <h3><strong>About Kadence</strong></h3>
   <p>Kadence is the AI-powered workplace platform turning companies’ two largest investments—<strong>people and space</strong>—into a durable competitive edge. Trusted by <strong>580+ organizations across 40 countries</strong>, we fuse space scheduling, team orchestration and deep workplace analytics in one seamless solution. With triple-digit growth our channel engine now needs its own leader.<br></p>
   <h3><strong>The Opportunity</strong></h3>
   <p>You’ll architect and run our global channel &amp; alliances machine—building “sell-through” velocity with resellers and “sell-with” lift alongside strategic partners (AV, UC &amp; smart-building). From zero-to-one programs to executive co-selling, you’ll own the full partner lifecycle and deliver outsized, capital-efficient revenue.<br></p>
   <h3><strong>Core Responsibilities</strong></h3>
   <ul>
    <li><strong>Channel Strategy &amp; GTM</strong> – initially craft and execute our N.American and W.European plan - covering <strong>sell-with</strong>&amp; <strong>sell-through</strong> motions; set tiering, MDF, SPIFs, comp alignment.</li>
    <li><strong>Enablement &amp; Readiness</strong> – deliver training, collateral, and executive briefing experiences that make partners self-sufficient and Kadence-obsessed.</li>
    <li><strong>Partner Management</strong> – own C-suite relationships with AV/UC manufacturers, smart-building vendors, and resellers; align roadmaps &amp; co-investment.</li>
    <li><strong>Joint Solutions &amp; Industry Plays</strong> – build packaged offers for priority verticals (tech, legal, life sciences) combining Kadence with ecosystem hardware &amp; AI.</li>
    <li><strong>Revenue &amp; Pipeline</strong> – hit channel ARR targets; track KPIs, surface insights, and optimize program economics.</li>
    <li><strong>Voice of Partner</strong> – feed integration gaps, pricing friction, and competitive intel back to Product &amp; Exec team for rapid alignment.<br></li>
   </ul>
   <h3><strong>What We’re Looking For</strong></h3>
   <ul>
    <li><strong>Channel rainmaker:</strong> 5-10 yrs building B2B SaaS and/or workplace-tech channels ($5-50 M ARR).</li>
    <li><strong>Operating-model fluency:</strong> deep understanding of VAR, distributor, MSP and ISV economics.</li>
    <li><strong>AI mindset:</strong> can spot where generative or predictive AI sharpens partner value props..</li>
    <li><strong>Full-stack operator:</strong> equally at ease spinning up a demo or modeling MDF ROI.</li>
    <li><strong>Global perspective:</strong> experience running programs across at least two major regions.<br></li>
   </ul>
   <h3><strong>Bonus Points</strong></h3>
   <ul>
    <li>Relationships with major technology manufacturers and target partners</li>
    <li>Prior success bundling software + hardware into subscription offerings for channel partners<br></li>
   </ul>
   <h3><strong>Why Kadence</strong></h3>
   <ul>
    <li>Hybrid (ability to work from where-ever works best for you) - ideally located in Salt Lake City (Utah) South East England, or Belfast (Northern Ireland)</li>
    <li>Competitive salary</li>
    <li>Equity stock options program</li>
    <li>Health insurance + 401k<br></li>
   </ul>
   <p>By joining Kadence, you\'ll have the opportunity to be part of a fast-growing, early-stage venture capital backed company. This means you\'ll have access to resources, mentorship, and a network of experienced professionals who are committed to helping you succeed.<br></p>
   <p>You\'ll also have the opportunity to play a critical role in shaping the future of the company and making a real impact in the Future of Work.<br></p>
   <p>We believe hybrid work will reshape the way the world works for the next century. We’re so passionate about this that we’ve crafted the <a href="http://hybridmanifesto.org/"><strong>Hybrid Manifesto</strong></a> - please check it out before applying for the role.</p>
   <p><em>Ready to make Kadence the centerpiece of every hybrid-ready workplace? Let’s talk.</em></p>
