INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (662, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/comet-2-c120b7ad-7729-4c38-8ecd-05ce080c822e/jobs/52294648-enterprise-account-executive-emea#content', 'Enterprise Account Executive (EMEA)', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/comet-2-c120b7ad-7729-4c38-8ecd-05ce080c822e?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlNhbGVzJTIwJTI2JTIwQnVzaW5lc3MlMjBEZXZlbG9wbWVudCJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/00abe223-4782-5717-a3d8-d5b196e4a563-1748741825', 'Comet', 'Sales & Business Development', 1749513600, '<div>
 <h2><strong>About Comet</strong></h2>
 <p>Comet is building the development platform for teams who want to ship robust, reliable, and responsible AI applications. Opik, our open source LLM evaluation framework, has quickly become one of the most popular tools in the space. Our experiment management platform is used by data scientists at companies like Uber, Netflix, and Etsy. Tens of thousands of researchers, engineers, academics, and hobbyists use Comet every day to build the future of AI.</p>
 <p>Working at Comet will give you access to the most exciting work being done in all areas of machine learning. Some of the top researchers and companies working on self-driving cars, drug discovery, particle research, diffusion models, and LLMs use Comet every day. Your work has the potential to accelerate the development of some of the most impactful technology in the world, and you will be doing it alongside a team of passionate, caring individuals. If that sounds exciting, Comet is the right place for you.</p>
 <p>Comet is backed by more than $63 million in venture capital funding and powers some of the best machine-learning teams in the world, including Netflix, Uber, Etsy, and Mobileye. We are a remote-first company with offices in New York City (USA) and Tel Aviv (Israel).</p>
</div>
<div>
 Comet is looking for an <strong>Enterprise Account Executive</strong> <strong>(EMEA) </strong>who will be responsible for prospecting and closing new business across EMEA. You will identify, nurture and close opportunities with both new and existing customers, manage forecasts and track customer data. You will be the driver with our prospective clients during the sales and customer expansion processes. You are comfortable engaging in both technical and business conversations at multiple levels of the organization, including CTO, VP of AI, Managers of AI, as well as machine learning practitioners. You enjoy bringing your product and technical knowledge to bear when articulating our business proposition, and your analytical nature means you bias towards winning business by showing how a client’s business model benefits from partnering with Comet. Your expertise will be critical in helping articulate the value of our products, working with the customer during the trial phase and handing off a strong relationship to our Customer Success team. Ideally, you come from a technical background and have sold products in the MLOps space before.
 <br><strong>Responsibilities:</strong>
</div>
<ul>
 <li>Drive new business opportunities from start to finish, from initial inquiry to forecasted pipeline to deal design and close.</li>
 <li>Develop and implement a sales strategy for your territory and/or targeted list of customers.</li>
 <li>Develop a deep understanding of the Comet value proposition in the market and be able to concisely articulate this value to prospects and customers.</li>
 <li>Constantly focus on prospecting into Enterprise companies (&gt;1000 employees) in EMEA to ensure long term success.</li>
 <li>Provide continuous updates on all active accounts and report on sales, activities, status and progress on a regular basis.</li>
 <li>Demonstrate technical knowledge of the ML and MLOps space and an appetite to learn new technologies, algorithms, and ideas from the field.</li>
 <li>Proactively work with your Technical Account Manager to design customer success and expansion strategies to drive new business from existing customers.</li>
 <li>Be willing and able to travel for client visits, conferences and presentations.</li>
</ul>
<div>
 <strong>Requirements:</strong>
</div>
<ul>
 <li>Ability to operate in a highly ambiguous and fast-paced environment.</li>
 <li>2+ experience in selling Enterprise focused technical solutions to technical buyers/users, preferably at a company selling to people directly involved in the ML/AI development process.</li>
 <li>Prior experience selling to data science teams.</li>
 <li>4+ years closing annual contracts of at least $100K/year, and handling yearly quotas of $1mm+.</li>
 <li>Strong technical background, ideally as a sales engineer or some technical educational program.</li>
 <li>Ability to understand <a href="http://comet.ml/">Comet</a> and build great relationships with highly technical customers.</li>
 <li>Prior experience at a fast-paced startup and able to work well in unstructured environments.</li>
 <li>Proven negotiation and closing skills.</li>
 <li>Nice to have: a technical background or formal data science training.</li>
</ul>
<div>
 <strong>What We Offer:</strong>
</div>
<ul>
 <li>Competitive salary based on proven experience, skills and location.</li>
 <li>Competitive benefits package.</li>
 <li>Flexible working hours and remote work options.</li>
 <li>Opportunities for professional growth and development.</li>
 <li>A collaborative and innovative work environment.</li>
 <li>The chance to work with cutting-edge technologies and projects.</li>
 <li><strong>A fully remote position in Europe,</strong> working with a global team (large presence in the US, Israel and Europe) - some flexibility with work hours is required.</li>
</ul>
<div>
 <p></p>
 <p><em>Comet is an equal-opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees without regard to race, religion, color, sex, gender identity, gender expression, sexual orientation, national origin, ancestry, citizenship status, uniform service member status, marital status, pregnancy, age, medical condition, physical or mental disability, genetic information/characteristics, and any other characteristic protected by State or Federal law.</em></p>
</div>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (663, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/wagmo/jobs/52291960-sales-enablement-manager#content', 'Sales Enablement Manager', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/wagmo?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlNhbGVzJTIwJTI2JTIwQnVzaW5lc3MlMjBEZXZlbG9wbWVudCJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/96e09e0a-f15c-5418-a7e8-01f23f94c77d-1748999739', 'Wagmo', 'Sales & Business Development', 1749513600, null);
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (664, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/warrant-2/jobs/52254984-business-development-representative#content', 'Business Development Representative', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/warrant-2?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlNhbGVzJTIwJTI2JTIwQnVzaW5lc3MlMjBEZXZlbG9wbWVudCJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/9e8505aa-f7df-5133-af5e-4ce7e2ea2a82-1750263216', 'Warrant', 'Sales & Business Development', 1749340800, '<div>
 <p><strong>About Warrant</strong></p>
 <p>Warrant is the first AI agent for marketing compliance. We help financial services, insurance, and real estate companies move fast <em>without compromising their brand or breaking the rules</em>. Whether launching a campaign, collaborating with influencers, or reviewing a landing page, Warrant gives instant compliance feedback, tracks version history, and keeps teams audit-ready.</p>
 <p>We’re backed by Brickyard, Capitalize VC, Techstars, and Vast Ventures—alongside operators and execs from Brex, Slope, and Mercury.</p>
 <p><strong>The Role: Business Development Representative</strong></p>
 <p>We’re looking for a high-energy Go-to-Market Generalist to join our founding team in Chattanooga. You’ll help us grow to 100+ customers by building pipeline, testing campaigns, and supporting sales, marketing, and partnership initiatives from the ground up.</p>
 <p>This role is <em>perfect</em> for someone who:</p>
 <ul>
  <li>Is startup-obsessed (maybe even a future/former founder) and wants an exclusive front-row seat to building a generational company from Pre-Seed</li>
  <li>Might’ve once considered law school—but craved something faster-paced and more impactful</li>
  <li>Wants to grind in the most exciting early-stage startup co-working space in the Southeast with 10+ other YC/venture-backed teams (SF who?)</li>
  <li>Thrives in a hands-on, fast-moving, IRL environment (yes, we mean in-person—not just Slack!)</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>What You’ll Do</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li><strong>Own outbound prospecting strategy and execution </strong>(cold calls, emails, LinkedIn) and partner with the CEO on early sales conversations</li>
  <li><strong>Qualify inbound leads </strong>through research and proactively set meetings</li>
  <li><strong>Lead and scale our referral programs</strong>, building repeatable deal flow through partnerships with law firms, agencies, and VCs</li>
  <li><strong>Assist in creating GTM assets</strong> to support sales, education, and brand-building</li>
  <li><strong>Engage directly with customers</strong> to build relationships and turn early users into power users</li>
  <li><strong>Refine our ideal customer persona</strong> through customer insights and shape the product roadmap alongside the founding team</li>
  <li><strong>Leverage AI </strong>to 10x your output and continue to recommend new systems and processes to reflect industry best practices</li>
  <li><strong>Host events, webinars, and strategic activations</strong>, with up to 25% domestic and international travel</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>You Might Be a Fit If You…</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Have 1–4 years of experience in B2B sales (former founders welcome!)</li>
  <li>Looking to move to an AE role within 1 year</li>
  <li>Are a clear communicator who can tell a story, sell a vision, and get people excited</li>
  <li>Love running fast experiments and digging into data</li>
  <li>Are energized by ambiguity, quick pivots, and building from scratch</li>
  <li>Skilled in using CRM systems, sales prospecting tools, Canva, Google Drive, and LinkedIn</li>
  <li>AI Power User (ChatGPT, Claude, etc.)</li>
  <li>Are curious about compliance or the intersection of law + marketing</li>
  <li>Experience at a tech SaaS startup or financial services/insurance is a huge plus</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Perks &amp; Benefits</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li>Competitive base salary with On-Target Earnings (OTE) of <strong>$65,000/year</strong>, with equity opportunity</li>
  <li>Health stipend and plans for vision/dental</li>
  <li>Unlimited paid time off</li>
  <li>Access to a pickleball court and brand-new gym with cold plunge &amp; sauna (with free group training sessions 3x a week)</li>
  <li>Team offsites + travel for top industry conferences domestically &amp; internationally</li>
 </ul>
 <p><strong>Location</strong></p>
 <ul>
  <li>In-person in <strong>Chattanooga, TN</strong> for 1 year (remote options available after 1 year)</li>
 </ul>
</div>');
INSERT INTO `parser-db`.job_postings (id, job_page_url, position_name, organization_url, logo_url, organization_title, labor_function, posted_date_unix, description_html) VALUES (665, 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/gorgias-com/jobs/52227761-account-executive-smb#content', 'Account Executive - SMB', 'https://jobs.techstars.com/companies/gorgias-com?filter=eyJqb2JfZnVuY3Rpb25zIjpbIlNhbGVzJTIwJTI2JTIwQnVzaW5lc3MlMjBEZXZlbG9wbWVudCJdfQ%3D%3D#content', 'https://cdn.getro.com/companies/aecd14bd-7bf3-5c22-a035-772e03fc55bf-1747616949', 'Gorgias', 'Sales & Business Development', 1749254400, '<p>Gorgias is the conversational AI platform for ecommerce that drives sales and resolves support inquiries. Trusted by over 15,000 ecommerce brands, Gorgias supports growing independent shops to globally recognizable brands.</p>
<p>Built for Shopify and powered by advanced ecommerce integrations, Gorgias\'s conversational AI understands your brand, tools, policies, and customers to drive personalized, 1-to-1 conversations — from editing orders and initiating returns to making product recommendations. Gorgias, where every customer interaction feels personal, support becomes sales, and conversations shape success.</p>
<h1>What You\'ll Do</h1>
<p>At Gorgias, you will be part of a dynamic and fast-growing sales team, helping e-commerce businesses elevate their customer support experience and boost sales. Your mission is to empower merchants to simplify and automate their support across multiple channels while creating lasting customer relationships. Here\'s how you\'ll make an impact:</p>
<h2>Your Day-to-Day</h2>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Own the Sales Journey:</strong> Lead discovery, demo, and pricing calls, showcasing the power of Gorgias tailored to each prospect’s specific needs.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Engage with Inbound Leads:</strong> Benefit from a well-developed lead generation team—your job will be less about hunting and more about guiding prospects through the buying journey.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Build Strong Relationships:</strong> Act as a trusted advisor, answering questions and overcoming objections to keep deals moving forward smoothly.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Drive Results Quickly:</strong> Thrive in a fast-paced environment where you’ll focus on closing deals efficiently while delivering an exceptional experience.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Collaborate with Teams:</strong> Work closely with marketing and product teams to align efforts and ensure the feedback loop supports continuous improvement.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Maintain Pipeline Hygiene:</strong> Follow up with prospects after demos, nurturing relationships and setting clear expectations for the next steps.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1><strong>Who You Are</strong></h1>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Sales Experience:</strong> 1+ years in tech sales, with a passion for fast-paced, high-growth environments.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Bilingual Proficiency:</strong> Excellent communication and writing skills in <strong>English</strong> and <strong>French</strong>.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>CRM Expertise:</strong> Understand the importance of CRM tools for maintaining data integrity and ensuring accurate forecasting.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Driven to Succeed:</strong> Thrive in dynamic settings, embracing challenges to refine and scale the sales process.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Deal Closer:</strong> Energized by fast-paced deals and the pursuit of ambitious goals.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Curious Learner:</strong> Maintain a deep sense of curiosity and hunger to grow your sales expertise.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Enjoy Selling:</strong> Selling comes naturally to you, and you\'re motivated to get even better.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Adaptable &amp; Efficient:</strong> Quickly grasp complex ideas, automate processes, and drive results.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Active Listener:</strong> Attuned to prospect needs, with a talent for spotting and leveraging opportunities.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p><strong>Action-Oriented:</strong> Execute quickly and efficiently to get things done.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Bonus Skills (Nice to Have):</strong></h2>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p>Proven track record of meeting or exceeding sales quotas.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Experience selling <strong>SaaS</strong> or working with <strong>e-commerce clients</strong>.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Knowledge of API and HTTP integrations.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Familiarity with MEDPICC methodology.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>Prior experience with customer support software.</p></li>
</ul>
<h1>Perks and Benefits</h1>
<ul>
 <li>
  <p>🏖️ 5-week vacation plus 2 weeks RTT</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>🤕 Paid sick leave</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>🌏 6 weeks full remote/year</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>🧸 Paid parental leave (16 weeks)</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>🍽️ Personal credit card to buy lunches (we use <a href="https://www.swile.co/en-FR" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">Swile</a>)</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>🏥 We provide private health insurance (we use <a href="https://alan.com/" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">Alan</a>)</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>💆🏻‍♀️ Get up to €700 to set up your workstation at home (working from home should feel breezy)</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>📚 Get up to €2000 of learning material and wellness support per year! This includes €1500 for learning material (such as books, courses, and individual coaching sessions) directly linked to your job scope, as well as a €500 wellness budget. Take advantage of these resources to grow in your role and prioritize your personal development and wellness.</p></li>
 <li>
  <p>🥰 Every quarter, we organize an online company-wide summit to discuss where we’re going and strengthen social bonds. Once per year we organize offsite team retreats and company retreats!</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Diversity &amp; Inclusion at Gorgias</strong><br>
 We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. We welcome applicants of all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives. At Gorgias, we believe that diverse teams drive innovation and better decision-making. We do not discriminate based on race, color, religion, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, age, or any other protected status.<br><br>
 If you need accommodations to participate in the application or interview process, perform essential job functions, or access other employment benefits, please contact us at <a href="#" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow">accommodation@gorgias.com</a>. Let’s grow together!</p>');
